var book = {
	"name": "Exodus",
	"numChapters": 40,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1534A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1534A\"></sup>These are the names of the sons of Israel who came to Egypt with Jacob, each with his household:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Dan and Naphtali, Gad and Asher.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All the descendants of Jacob were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1538B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1538B\"></sup>seventy persons; Joseph was already in Egypt.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1539C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1539C\"></sup>Joseph died, and all his brothers and all that generation.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1540D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1540D\"></sup>But the people of Israel were fruitful and increased greatly; they multiplied and grew exceedingly strong, so that the land was filled with them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now there arose a new king over Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1541E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1541E\"></sup>who did not know Joseph.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he said to his people, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1542F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1542F\"></sup>the people of Israel are too many and too mighty for us.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1543G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1543G\"></sup>Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1543H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1543H\"></sup>let us deal shrewdly with them, lest they multiply, and, if war breaks out, they join our enemies and fight against us and escape from the land.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Therefore they set taskmasters over them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1544I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1544I\"></sup>to afflict them with heavy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1544J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1544J\"></sup>burdens. They built for Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1544K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1544K\"></sup>store cities, Pithom and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1544L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1544L\"></sup>Raamses.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the more they were oppressed, the more they multiplied and the more they spread abroad. And the Egyptians were in dread of the people of Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So they ruthlessly made the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1546M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1546M\"></sup>work as slaves",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1547N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1547N\"></sup>made their lives bitter with hard service, in mortar and brick, and in all kinds of work in the field. In all their work they ruthlessly made them work as slaves.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the king of Egypt said to the Hebrew midwives, one of whom was named Shiphrah and the other Puah,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“When you serve as midwife to the Hebrew women and see them on the birthstool, if it is a son, you shall kill him, but if it is a daughter, she shall live.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the midwives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1550O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1550O\"></sup>feared God and did not do as the king of Egypt commanded them, but let the male children live.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So the king of Egypt called the midwives and said to them, “Why have you done this, and let the male children live?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The midwives said to Pharaoh, “Because the Hebrew women are not like the Egyptian women, for they are vigorous and give birth before the midwife comes to them.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1553P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1553P\"></sup>So God dealt well with the midwives. And the people multiplied and grew very strong.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And because the midwives feared God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1554Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1554Q\"></sup>he gave them families.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Pharaoh commanded all his people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1555R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1555R\"></sup>“Every son that is born to the Hebrews you shall cast into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1555S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1555S\"></sup>the Nile, but you shall let every daughter live.”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Now a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1556A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1556A\"></sup>man from the house of Levi went and took as his wife a Levite woman.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The woman conceived and bore a son, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1557B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1557B\"></sup>when she saw that he was a fine child, she hid him three months.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When she could hide him no longer, she took for him a basket made of bulrushes and daubed it with bitumen and pitch. She put the child in it and placed it among the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1558C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1558C\"></sup>reeds by the river bank.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1559D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1559D\"></sup>his sister stood at a distance to know what would be done to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now the daughter of Pharaoh came down to bathe at the river, while her young women walked beside the river. She saw the basket among the reeds and sent her servant woman, and she took it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When she opened it, she saw the child, and behold, the baby was crying. She took pity on him and said, “This is one of the Hebrews' children.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then his sister said to Pharaoh's daughter, “Shall I go and call you a nurse from the Hebrew women to nurse the child for you?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Pharaoh's daughter said to her, “Go.” So the girl went and called the child's mother.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Pharaoh's daughter said to her, “Take this child away and nurse him for me, and I will give you your wages.” So the woman took the child and nursed him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When the child grew older, she brought him to Pharaoh's daughter, and he became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1565E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1565E\"></sup>her son. She named him Moses, “Because,” she said, “I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1565F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1565F\"></sup>drew him out of the water.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>One day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1566G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1566G\"></sup>when Moses had grown up, he went out to his people and looked on their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1566H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1566H\"></sup>burdens, and he saw an Egyptian beating a Hebrew, one of his people.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He looked this way and that, and seeing no one, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1567I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1567I\"></sup>struck down the Egyptian and hid him in the sand.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1568J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1568J\"></sup>he went out the next day, behold, two Hebrews were struggling together. And he said to the man in the wrong, “Why do you strike your companion?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1569K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1569K\"></sup>“Who made you a prince and a judge over us? Do you mean to kill me as you killed the Egyptian?” Then Moses was afraid, and thought, “Surely the thing is known.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Pharaoh heard of it, he sought to kill Moses. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1570L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1570L\"></sup>Moses fled from Pharaoh and stayed in the land of Midian. And he sat down by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1570M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1570M\"></sup>a well.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1571N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1571N\"></sup>priest of Midian had seven daughters, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1571O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1571O\"></sup>they came and drew water and filled the troughs to water their father's flock.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The shepherds came and drove them away, but Moses stood up and saved them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1572P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1572P\"></sup>watered their flock.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they came home to their father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1573Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1573Q\"></sup>Reuel, he said, “How is it that you have come home so soon today?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They said, “An Egyptian delivered us out of the hand of the shepherds and even drew water for us and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1574R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1574R\"></sup>watered the flock.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He said to his daughters, “Then where is he? Why have you left the man? Call him, that he may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1575S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1575S\"></sup>eat bread.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Moses was content to dwell with the man, and he gave Moses his daughter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1576T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1576T\"></sup>Zipporah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>She gave birth to a son, and he called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1577U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1577U\"></sup>Gershom, for he said, “I have been a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1577V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1577V\"></sup>sojourner in a foreign land.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1578W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1578W\"></sup>During those many days the king of Egypt died, and the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1578X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1578X\"></sup>groaned because of their slavery and cried out for help. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1578Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1578Y\"></sup>Their cry for rescue from slavery came up to God.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1579Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1579Z\"></sup>God heard their groaning, and God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1579AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1579AA\"></sup>remembered his covenant with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1579AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1579AB\"></sup>Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1580AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1580AC\"></sup>saw the people of Israel—and God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1580AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1580AD\"></sup>knew."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now Moses was keeping the flock of his father-in-law, Jethro, the priest of Midian, and he led his flock to the west side of the wilderness and came to Horeb, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1581A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1581A\"></sup>mountain of God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1582B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1582B\"></sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1582C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1582C\"></sup>the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him in a flame of fire out of the midst of a bush. He looked, and behold, the bush was burning, yet it was not consumed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Moses said, “I will turn aside to see this great sight, why the bush is not burned.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that he turned aside to see, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1584D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1584D\"></sup>God called to him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1584E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1584E\"></sup>out of the bush, “Moses, Moses!” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he said, “Do not come near; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1585F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1585F\"></sup>take your sandals off your feet, for the place on which you are standing is holy ground.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1586G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1586G\"></sup>“I am the God of your father, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.” And Moses hid his face, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1586H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1586H\"></sup>he was afraid to look at God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1587I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1587I\"></sup>“I have surely seen the affliction of my people who are in Egypt and have heard their cry because of their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1587J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1587J\"></sup>taskmasters. I know their sufferings,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1588K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1588K\"></sup>I have come down to deliver them out of the hand of the Egyptians and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1588L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1588L\"></sup>to bring them up out of that land to a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1588M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1588M\"></sup>good and broad land, a land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1588N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1588N\"></sup>flowing with milk and honey, to the place of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1588O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1588O\"></sup>the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And now, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1589P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1589P\"></sup>the cry of the people of Israel has come to me, and I have also seen the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1589Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1589Q\"></sup>oppression with which the Egyptians oppress them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1590R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1590R\"></sup>Come, I will send you to Pharaoh that you may bring my people, the children of Israel, out of Egypt.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Moses said to God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1591S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1591S\"></sup>“Who am I that I should go to Pharaoh and bring the children of Israel out of Egypt?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1592T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1592T\"></sup>“But I will be with you, and this shall be the sign for you, that I have sent you: when you have brought the people out of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1592U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1592U\"></sup>you shall serve God on this mountain.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Moses said to God, “If I come to the people of Israel and say to them, ‘The God of your fathers has sent me to you,’ and they ask me, ‘What is his name?’ what shall I say to them?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>God said to Moses, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">I am who I am</span>.” And he said, “Say this to the people of Israel: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1594V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1594V\"></sup>‘<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">I am</span> has sent me to you.’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>God also said to Moses, “Say this to the people of Israel: ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1595W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1595W\"></sup>God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has sent me to you.’ This is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1595X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1595X\"></sup>my name forever, and thus I am to be remembered throughout all generations.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Go and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1596Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1596Y\"></sup>gather the elders of Israel together and say to them, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, of Isaac, and of Jacob, has appeared to me, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1596Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1596Z\"></sup>“I have observed you and what has been done to you in Egypt,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and I promise that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1597AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1597AA\"></sup>I will bring you up out of the affliction of Egypt to the land of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, a land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1597AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1597AB\"></sup>flowing with milk and honey.”’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1598AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1598AC\"></sup>they will listen to your voice, and you and the elders of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1598AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1598AD\"></sup>shall go to the king of Egypt and say to him, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1598AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1598AE\"></sup>met with us; and now, please let us go a three days' journey into the wilderness, that we may sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But I know that the king of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1599AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1599AF\"></sup>will not let you go unless compelled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1599AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1599AG\"></sup>by a mighty hand.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1600AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1600AH\"></sup>I will stretch out my hand and strike Egypt with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1600AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1600AI\"></sup>all the wonders that I will do in it; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1600AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1600AJ\"></sup>after that he will let you go.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1601AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1601AK\"></sup>I will give this people favor in the sight of the Egyptians; and when you go, you shall not go empty,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>but each woman shall ask of her neighbor, and any woman who lives in her house, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1602AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1602AL\"></sup>silver and gold jewelry, and for clothing. You shall put them on your sons and on your daughters. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1602AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1602AM\"></sup>you shall plunder the Egyptians.”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Then Moses answered, “But behold, they will not believe me or listen to my voice, for they will say, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not appear to you.’”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “What is that in your hand?” He said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1604A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1604A\"></sup>“A staff.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he said, “Throw it on the ground.” So he threw it on the ground, and it became a serpent, and Moses ran from it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Put out your hand and catch it by the tail”—so he put out his hand and caught it, and it became a staff in his hand—",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“that they may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1607B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1607B\"></sup>believe that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1607C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1607C\"></sup>the God of their fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has appeared to you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Again, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Put your hand inside your cloak.” And he put his hand inside his cloak, and when he took it out, behold, his hand was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1608D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1608D\"></sup>leprous like snow.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then God said, “Put your hand back inside your cloak.” So he put his hand back inside his cloak, and when he took it out, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1609E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1609E\"></sup>it was restored like the rest of his flesh.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“If they will not believe you,” God said, “or listen to the first sign, they may believe the latter sign.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If they will not believe even these two signs or listen to your voice, you shall take some water from the Nile and pour it on the dry ground, and the water that you shall take from the Nile <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1611F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1611F\"></sup>will become blood on the dry ground.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Oh, my Lord, I am not eloquent, either in the past or since you have spoken to your servant, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1612G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1612G\"></sup>I am slow of speech and of tongue.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Who has made man's mouth? Who makes him mute, or deaf, or seeing, or blind? Is it not I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now therefore go, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1614H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1614H\"></sup>I will be with your mouth and teach you what you shall speak.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But he said, “Oh, my Lord, please send someone else.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Moses and he said, “Is there not Aaron, your brother, the Levite? I know that he can speak well. Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1616I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1616I\"></sup>he is coming out to meet you, and when he sees you, he will be glad in his heart.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1617J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1617J\"></sup>You shall speak to him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1617K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1617K\"></sup>put the words in his mouth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1617L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1617L\"></sup>I will be with your mouth and with his mouth and will teach you both what to do.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1618M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1618M\"></sup>He shall speak for you to the people, and he shall be your mouth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1618N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1618N\"></sup>you shall be as God to him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And take in your hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1619O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1619O\"></sup>this staff, with which you shall do the signs.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moses went back to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1620P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1620P\"></sup>Jethro his father-in-law and said to him, “Please let me go back to my brothers in Egypt to see whether they are still alive.” And Jethro said to Moses, “Go in peace.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses in Midian, “Go back to Egypt, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1621Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1621Q\"></sup>all the men who were seeking your life are dead.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Moses took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1622R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1622R\"></sup>his wife and his sons and had them ride on a donkey, and went back to the land of Egypt. And Moses took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1622S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1622S\"></sup>the staff of God in his hand.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “When you go back to Egypt, see that you do before Pharaoh all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1623T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1623T\"></sup>miracles that I have put in your power. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1623U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1623U\"></sup>I will harden his heart, so that he will not let the people go.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then you shall say to Pharaoh, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1624V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1624V\"></sup>Israel is my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1624W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1624W\"></sup>firstborn son,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and I say to you, “Let my son go that he may serve me.” If you refuse to let him go, behold, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1625X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1625X\"></sup>will kill your firstborn son.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>At a lodging place on the way <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1626Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1626Y\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> met him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1626Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1626Z\"></sup>sought to put him to death.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1627AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1627AA\"></sup>Zipporah took a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1627AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1627AB\"></sup>flint and cut off her son's foreskin and touched Moses' feet with it and said, “Surely you are a bridegroom of blood to me!”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So he let him alone. It was then that she said, “A bridegroom of blood,” because of the circumcision.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Aaron, “Go into the wilderness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1629AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1629AC\"></sup>to meet Moses.” So he went and met him at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1629AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1629AD\"></sup>mountain of God and kissed him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1630AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1630AE\"></sup>told Aaron all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with which he had sent him to speak, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1630AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1630AF\"></sup>the signs that he had commanded him to do.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Moses and Aaron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1631AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1631AG\"></sup>went and gathered together all the elders of the people of Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1632AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1632AH\"></sup>Aaron spoke all the words that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to Moses and did the signs in the sight of the people.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1633AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1633AI\"></sup>believed; and when they heard that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1633AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1633AJ\"></sup>visited the people of Israel and that he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1633AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1633AK\"></sup>seen their affliction, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1633AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1633AL\"></sup>they bowed their heads and worshiped."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Afterward Moses and Aaron went and said to Pharaoh, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Let my people go, that they may hold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1634A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1634A\"></sup>a feast to me in the wilderness.’”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Pharaoh said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1635B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1635B\"></sup>“Who is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that I should obey his voice and let Israel go? I do not know the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1635C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1635C\"></sup>I will not let Israel go.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then they said, “The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1636D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1636D\"></sup>God of the Hebrews has met with us. Please let us go a three days' journey into the wilderness that we may sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, lest he fall upon us with pestilence or with the sword.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the king of Egypt said to them, “Moses and Aaron, why do you take the people away from their work? Get back to your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1637E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1637E\"></sup>burdens.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Pharaoh said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1638F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1638F\"></sup>the people of the land are now many, and you make them rest from their burdens!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The same day Pharaoh commanded the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1639G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1639G\"></sup>taskmasters of the people and their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1639H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1639H\"></sup>foremen,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“You shall no longer give the people straw to make bricks, as in the past; let them go and gather straw for themselves.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the number of bricks that they made in the past you shall impose on them, you shall by no means reduce it, for they are idle. Therefore they cry, ‘Let us go and offer sacrifice to our God.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Let heavier work be laid on the men that they may labor at it and pay no regard to lying words.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1643I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1643I\"></sup>taskmasters and the foremen of the people went out and said to the people, “Thus says Pharaoh, ‘I will not give you straw.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Go and get your straw yourselves wherever you can find it, but your work will not be reduced in the least.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So the people were scattered throughout all the land of Egypt to gather stubble for straw.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1646J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1646J\"></sup>taskmasters were urgent, saying, “Complete your work, your daily task each day, as when there was straw.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the foremen of the people of Israel, whom Pharaoh's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1647K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1647K\"></sup>taskmasters had set over them, were beaten and were asked, “Why have you not done all your task of making bricks today and yesterday, as in the past?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the foremen of the people of Israel came and cried to Pharaoh, “Why do you treat your servants like this?",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>No straw is given to your servants, yet they say to us, ‘Make bricks!’ And behold, your servants are beaten; but the fault is in your own people.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But he said, “You are idle, you are idle; that is why you say, ‘Let us go and sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Go now and work. No straw will be given you, but you must still deliver the same number of bricks.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The foremen of the people of Israel saw that they were in trouble when they said, “You shall by no means reduce your number of bricks, your daily task each day.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They met Moses and Aaron, who were waiting for them, as they came out from Pharaoh;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1654L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1654L\"></sup>they said to them, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> look on you and judge, because you have made us stink in the sight of Pharaoh and his servants, and have put a sword in their hand to kill us.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Moses turned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “O Lord, why have you done evil to this people? Why did you ever send me?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in your name, he has done evil to this people, and you have not delivered your people at all.”"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Now you shall see what I will do to Pharaoh; for with a strong hand he will send them out, and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1657A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1657A\"></sup>a strong hand he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1657B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1657B\"></sup>drive them out of his land.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>God spoke to Moses and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1658C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1658C\"></sup>“I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I appeared to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1659D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1659D\"></sup>God Almighty, but by my name the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1659E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1659E\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> I did not make myself known to them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1660F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1660F\"></sup>I also established my covenant with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1660G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1660G\"></sup>to give them the land of Canaan, the land in which they lived as sojourners.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1661H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1661H\"></sup>I have heard the groaning of the people of Israel whom the Egyptians hold as slaves, and I have remembered my covenant.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Say therefore to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1662I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1662I\"></sup>‘I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1662J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1662J\"></sup>I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, and I will deliver you from slavery to them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1662K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1662K\"></sup>I will redeem you with an outstretched arm and with great acts of judgment.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1663L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1663L\"></sup>will take you to be my people, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1663M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1663M\"></sup>I will be your God, and you shall know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1663N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1663N\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has brought you out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1663O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1663O\"></sup>from under the burdens of the Egyptians.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I will bring you into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1664P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1664P\"></sup>the land that I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1664Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1664Q\"></sup>swore to give to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob. I will give it to you for a possession. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1664R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1664R\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Moses spoke thus to the people of Israel, but they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1665S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1665S\"></sup>did not listen to Moses, because of their broken spirit and harsh slavery.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Go in, tell Pharaoh king of Egypt to let the people of Israel go out of his land.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Behold, the people of Israel have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1668T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1668T\"></sup>not listened to me. How then shall Pharaoh listen to me, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1668U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1668U\"></sup>I am of uncircumcised lips?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron and gave them a charge about the people of Israel and about Pharaoh king of Egypt: to bring the people of Israel out of the land of Egypt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These are the heads of their fathers' houses: the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1670V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1670V\"></sup>sons of Reuben, the firstborn of Israel: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi; these are the clans of Reuben.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1671W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1671W\"></sup>sons of Simeon: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul, the son of a Canaanite woman; these are the clans of Simeon.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These are the names of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1672X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1672X\"></sup>sons of Levi according to their generations: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari, the years of the life of Levi being 137 years.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1673Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1673Y\"></sup>sons of Gershon: Libni and Shimei, by their clans.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1674Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1674Z\"></sup>sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, the years of the life of Kohath being 133 years.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1675AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1675AA\"></sup>sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the clans of the Levites according to their generations.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1676AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1676AB\"></sup>Amram took as his wife Jochebed his father's sister, and she bore him Aaron and Moses, the years of the life of Amram being 137 years.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1677AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1677AC\"></sup>The sons of Izhar: Korah, Nepheg, and Zichri.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1678AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1678AD\"></sup>sons of Uzziel: Mishael, Elzaphan, and Sithri.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Aaron took as his wife Elisheba, the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1679AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1679AE\"></sup>Amminadab and the sister of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1679AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1679AF\"></sup>Nahshon, and she bore him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1679AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1679AG\"></sup>Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1680AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1680AH\"></sup>sons of Korah: Assir, Elkanah, and Abiasaph; these are the clans of the Korahites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Eleazar, Aaron's son, took as his wife one of the daughters of Putiel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1681AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1681AI\"></sup>she bore him Phinehas. These are the heads of the fathers' houses of the Levites by their clans.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>These are the Aaron and Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1682AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1682AJ\"></sup>to whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said: “Bring out the people of Israel from the land of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1682AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1682AK\"></sup>by their hosts.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It was they who spoke to Pharaoh king of Egypt about bringing out the people of Israel from Egypt, this Moses and this Aaron.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>On the day when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses in the land of Egypt,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1685AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1685AL\"></sup>“I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1685AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1685AM\"></sup>tell Pharaoh king of Egypt all that I say to you.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1686AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1686AN\"></sup>I am of uncircumcised lips. How will Pharaoh listen to me?”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “See, I have made you like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1687A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1687A\"></sup>God to Pharaoh, and your brother Aaron shall be your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1687B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1687B\"></sup>prophet.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1688C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1688C\"></sup>You shall speak all that I command you, and your brother Aaron shall tell Pharaoh to let the people of Israel go out of his land.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1689D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1689D\"></sup>I will harden Pharaoh's heart, and though I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1689E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1689E\"></sup>multiply my signs and wonders in the land of Egypt,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Pharaoh will not listen to you. Then I will lay my hand on Egypt and bring my hosts, my people the children of Israel, out of the land of Egypt by great acts of judgment.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Egyptians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1691F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1691F\"></sup>shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, when I stretch out my hand against Egypt and bring out the people of Israel from among them.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moses and Aaron did so; they did just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Moses was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1693G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1693G\"></sup>eighty years old, and Aaron eighty-three years old, when they spoke to Pharaoh.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When Pharaoh says to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1695H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1695H\"></sup>‘Prove yourselves by working a miracle,’ then you shall say to Aaron, ‘Take your staff and cast it down before Pharaoh, that it may become a serpent.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Moses and Aaron went to Pharaoh and did just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded. Aaron cast down his staff before Pharaoh and his servants, and it became a serpent.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Pharaoh summoned the wise men and the sorcerers, and they, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1697I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1697I\"></sup>magicians of Egypt, also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1697J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1697J\"></sup>did the same by their secret arts.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For each man cast down his staff, and they became serpents. But Aaron's staff swallowed up their staffs.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Still <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1699K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1699K\"></sup>Pharaoh's heart was hardened, and he would not listen to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1699L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1699L\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Pharaoh's heart is hardened; he refuses to let the people go.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1701M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1701M\"></sup>Go to Pharaoh in the morning, as he is going out to the water. Stand on the bank of the Nile to meet him, and take in your hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1701N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1701N\"></sup>the staff that turned into a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1701O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1701O\"></sup>serpent.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And you shall say to him, ‘The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1702P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1702P\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, sent me to you, saying, “Let my people go, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1702Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1702Q\"></sup>that they may serve me in the wilderness.” But so far, you have not obeyed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “By this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1703R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1703R\"></sup>you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: behold, with the staff that is in my hand I will strike the water that is in the Nile, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1703S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1703S\"></sup>it shall turn into blood.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The fish in the Nile shall die, and the Nile will stink, and the Egyptians will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1704T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1704T\"></sup>grow weary of drinking water from the Nile.”’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Say to Aaron, ‘Take your staff and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1705U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1705U\"></sup>stretch out your hand over the waters of Egypt, over their rivers, their canals, and their ponds, and all their pools of water, so that they may become blood, and there shall be blood throughout all the land of Egypt, even in vessels of wood and in vessels of stone.’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Moses and Aaron did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded. In the sight of Pharaoh and in the sight of his servants he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1706V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1706V\"></sup>lifted up the staff and struck the water in the Nile, and all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1706W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1706W\"></sup>water in the Nile turned into blood.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the fish in the Nile died, and the Nile stank, so that the Egyptians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1707X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1707X\"></sup>could not drink water from the Nile. There was blood throughout all the land of Egypt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1708Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1708Y\"></sup>the magicians of Egypt did the same by their secret arts. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1708Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1708Z\"></sup>Pharaoh's heart remained hardened, and he would not listen to them, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1708AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1708AA\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Pharaoh turned and went into his house, and he did not take even this to heart.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And all the Egyptians dug along the Nile for water to drink, for they could not drink the water of the Nile.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Seven full days passed after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had struck the Nile."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span> Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go in to Pharaoh and say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Let my people go, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1712A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1712A\"></sup>they may serve me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But if you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1713B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1713B\"></sup>refuse to let them go, behold, I will plague all your country with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1713C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1713C\"></sup>frogs.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Nile shall swarm with frogs that shall come up into your house and into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1714D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1714D\"></sup>your bedroom and on your bed and into the houses of your servants and your people, and into your ovens and your kneading bowls.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The frogs shall come up on you and on your people and on all your servants.”’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup> And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Say to Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1716E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1716E\"></sup>‘Stretch out your hand with your staff over the rivers, over the canals and over the pools, and make frogs come up on the land of Egypt!’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Aaron stretched out his hand over the waters of Egypt, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1717F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1717F\"></sup>the frogs came up and covered the land of Egypt.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1718G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1718G\"></sup>the magicians did the same by their secret arts and made frogs come up on the land of Egypt.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Pharaoh called Moses and Aaron and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1719H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1719H\"></sup>“Plead with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to take away the frogs from me and from my people, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1719I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1719I\"></sup>I will let the people go to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Moses said to Pharaoh, “Be pleased to command me when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1720J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1720J\"></sup>I am to plead for you and for your servants and for your people, that the frogs be cut off from you and your houses and be left only in the Nile.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he said, “Tomorrow.” Moses said, “Be it as you say, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1721K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1721K\"></sup>that you may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1721L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1721L\"></sup>there is no one like the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The frogs shall go away from you and your houses and your servants and your people. They shall be left only in the Nile.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Moses and Aaron went out from Pharaoh, and Moses cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> about the frogs, as he had agreed with Pharaoh.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did according to the word of Moses. The frogs died out in the houses, the courtyards, and the fields.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they gathered them together in heaps, and the land stank.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But when Pharaoh saw that there was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1726M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1726M\"></sup>respite, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1726N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1726N\"></sup>hardened his heart and would not listen to them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Say to Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1727O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1727O\"></sup>‘Stretch out your staff and strike the dust of the earth, so that it may become gnats in all the land of Egypt.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they did so. Aaron stretched out his hand with his staff and struck the dust of the earth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1728P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1728P\"></sup>there were gnats on man and beast. All the dust of the earth became gnats in all the land of Egypt.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1729Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1729Q\"></sup>magicians tried by their secret arts to produce gnats, but they could not. So there were gnats on man and beast.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the magicians said to Pharaoh, “This is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1730R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1730R\"></sup>the finger of God.” But Pharaoh's heart was hardened, and he would not listen to them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1731S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1731S\"></sup>“Rise up early in the morning and present yourself to Pharaoh, as he goes out to the water, and say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1731T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1731T\"></sup>“Let my people go, that they may serve me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Or else, if you will not let my people go, behold, I will send swarms of flies on you and your servants and your people, and into your houses. And the houses of the Egyptians shall be filled with swarms of flies, and also the ground on which they stand.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But on that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1733U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1733U\"></sup>I will set apart the land of Goshen, where my people dwell, so that no swarms of flies shall be there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1733V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1733V\"></sup>that you may know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the midst of the earth.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Thus I will put a division between my people and your people. Tomorrow this sign shall happen.”’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did so. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1735W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1735W\"></sup>There came great swarms of flies into the house of Pharaoh and into his servants' houses. Throughout all the land of Egypt the land was ruined by the swarms of flies.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Pharaoh called Moses and Aaron and said, “Go, sacrifice to your God within the land.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Moses said, “It would not be right to do so, for the offerings we shall sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God are an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1737X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1737X\"></sup>abomination to the Egyptians. If we sacrifice offerings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1737Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1737Y\"></sup>abominable to the Egyptians before their eyes, will they not stone us?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>We must go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1738Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1738Z\"></sup>three days' journey into the wilderness and sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1738AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1738AA\"></sup>as he tells us.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Pharaoh said, “I will let you go to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in the wilderness; only you must not go very far away. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1739AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1739AB\"></sup>Plead for me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Moses said, “Behold, I am going out from you and I will plead with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that the swarms of flies may depart from Pharaoh, from his servants, and from his people, tomorrow. Only let not Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1740AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1740AC\"></sup>cheat again by not letting the people go to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Moses went out from Pharaoh and prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did as Moses asked, and removed the swarms of flies from Pharaoh, from his servants, and from his people; not one remained.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1743AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1743AD\"></sup>hardened his heart this time also, and did not let the people go."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1744A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1744A\"></sup>“Go in to Pharaoh and say to him, ‘Thus says <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1744B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1744B\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, “Let my people go, that they may serve me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For if you refuse to let them go and still hold them,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1746C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1746C\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will fall with a very severe plague upon your livestock that are in the field, the horses, the donkeys, the camels, the herds, and the flocks.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1747D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1747D\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make a distinction between the livestock of Israel and the livestock of Egypt, so that nothing of all that belongs to the people of Israel shall die.”’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set a time, saying, “Tomorrow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do this thing in the land.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the next day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did this thing. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1749E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1749E\"></sup>All the livestock of the Egyptians died, but not one of the livestock of the people of Israel died.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Pharaoh sent, and behold, not one of the livestock of Israel was dead. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1750F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1750F\"></sup>the heart of Pharaoh was hardened, and he did not let the people go.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron, “Take handfuls of soot from the kiln, and let Moses throw them in the air in the sight of Pharaoh.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It shall become fine dust over all the land of Egypt, and become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1752G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1752G\"></sup>boils breaking out in sores on man and beast throughout all the land of Egypt.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they took soot from the kiln and stood before Pharaoh. And Moses threw it in the air, and it became boils breaking out in sores on man and beast.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1754H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1754H\"></sup>the magicians could not stand before Moses because of the boils, for the boils came upon the magicians and upon all the Egyptians.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1755I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1755I\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hardened the heart of Pharaoh, and he did not listen to them, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1755J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1755J\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to Moses.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1756K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1756K\"></sup>“Rise up early in the morning and present yourself before Pharaoh and say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, “Let my people go, that they may serve me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For this time I will send all my plagues on you yourself, and on your servants and your people, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1757L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1757L\"></sup>that you may know that there is none like me in all the earth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For by now I could have put out my hand and struck you and your people with pestilence, and you would have been cut off from the earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1759M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1759M\"></sup>But for this purpose I have raised you up, to show you my power, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1759N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1759N\"></sup>that my name may be proclaimed in all the earth.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1760O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1760O\"></sup>You are still exalting yourself against my people and will not let them go.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Behold, about this time tomorrow I will cause very heavy hail to fall, such as never has been in Egypt from the day it was founded until now.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now therefore send, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1762P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1762P\"></sup>get your livestock and all that you have in the field into safe shelter, for every man and beast that is in the field and is not brought home will die when the hail falls on them.”’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then whoever feared the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> among the servants of Pharaoh hurried his slaves and his livestock into the houses,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but whoever did not pay attention to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> left his slaves and his livestock in the field.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Stretch out your hand toward heaven, so that there may be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1765Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1765Q\"></sup>hail in all the land of Egypt, on man and beast and every plant of the field, in the land of Egypt.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Moses stretched out his staff toward heaven, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1766R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1766R\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent thunder and hail, and fire ran down to the earth. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rained hail upon the land of Egypt.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>There was hail and fire flashing continually in the midst of the hail, very heavy hail, such as had never been in all the land of Egypt since it became a nation.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The hail struck down everything that was in the field in all the land of Egypt, both man and beast. And the hail <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1768S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1768S\"></sup>struck down every plant of the field and broke every tree of the field.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1769T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1769T\"></sup>Only in the land of Goshen, where the people of Israel were, was there no hail.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then Pharaoh sent and called Moses and Aaron and said to them, “This time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1770U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1770U\"></sup>I have sinned; the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1770V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1770V\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is in the right, and I and my people are in the wrong.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1771W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1771W\"></sup>Plead with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for there has been enough of God's thunder and hail. I will let you go, and you shall stay no longer.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Moses said to him, “As soon as I have gone out of the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1772X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1772X\"></sup>I will stretch out my hands to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The thunder will cease, and there will be no more hail, so that you may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1772Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1772Y\"></sup>the earth is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But as for you and your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1773Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1773Z\"></sup>I know that you do not yet fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>(The flax and the barley were struck down, for the barley was in the ear and the flax was in bud.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But the wheat and the emmer were not struck down, for they are late in coming up.)",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So Moses went out of the city from Pharaoh and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1776AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1776AA\"></sup>stretched out his hands to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the thunder and the hail ceased, and the rain no longer poured upon the earth.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But when Pharaoh saw that the rain and the hail and the thunder had ceased, he sinned yet again and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1777AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1777AB\"></sup>hardened his heart, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1777AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1777AC\"></sup>he and his servants.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1778AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1778AD\"></sup>the heart of Pharaoh was hardened, and he did not let the people of Israel go, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken through Moses."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go in to Pharaoh, for I have hardened his heart and the heart of his servants, that I may show these signs of mine among them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1780A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1780A\"></sup>that you may tell in the hearing of your son and of your grandson how I have dealt harshly with the Egyptians and what signs I have done among them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1780B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1780B\"></sup>that you may know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Moses and Aaron went in to Pharaoh and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, ‘How long will you refuse to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1781C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1781C\"></sup>humble yourself before me? Let my people go, that they may serve me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For if you refuse to let my people go, behold, tomorrow I will bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1782D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1782D\"></sup>locusts into your country,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and they shall cover the face of the land, so that no one can see the land. And they shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1783E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1783E\"></sup>eat what is left to you after the hail, and they shall eat every tree of yours that grows in the field,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and they shall fill <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1784F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1784F\"></sup>your houses and the houses of all your servants and of all the Egyptians, as neither your fathers nor your grandfathers have seen, from the day they came on earth to this day.’” Then he turned and went out from Pharaoh.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Pharaoh's servants said to him, “How long shall this man be a snare to us? Let the men go, that they may serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God. Do you not yet understand that Egypt is ruined?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Moses and Aaron were brought back to Pharaoh. And he said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1786G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1786G\"></sup>“Go, serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. But which ones are to go?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Moses said, “We will go with our young and our old. We will go with our sons and daughters and with our flocks and herds, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1787H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1787H\"></sup>we must hold a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But he said to them, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you, if ever I let you and your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1788I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1788I\"></sup>little ones go! Look, you have some evil purpose in mind.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>No! Go, the men among you, and serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for that is what you are asking.” And they were driven out from Pharaoh's presence.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1790J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1790J\"></sup>“Stretch out your hand over the land of Egypt for the locusts, so that they may come upon the land of Egypt and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1790K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1790K\"></sup>eat every plant in the land, all that the hail has left.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Moses stretched out his staff over the land of Egypt, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought an east wind upon the land all that day and all that night. When it was morning, the east wind had brought the locusts.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1792L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1792L\"></sup>The locusts came up over all the land of Egypt and settled on the whole country of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1792M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1792M\"></sup>such a dense swarm of locusts as had never been before, nor ever will be again.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They covered the face of the whole land, so that the land was darkened, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1793N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1793N\"></sup>they ate all the plants in the land and all the fruit of the trees that the hail had left. Not a green thing remained, neither tree nor plant of the field, through all the land of Egypt.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Pharaoh hastily called Moses and Aaron and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1794O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1794O\"></sup>“I have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and against you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now therefore, forgive my sin, please, only this once, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1795P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1795P\"></sup>plead with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God only to remove this death from me.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1796Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1796Q\"></sup>he went out from Pharaoh and pleaded with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turned the wind into a very strong west wind, which lifted the locusts and drove them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1797R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1797R\"></sup>into the Red Sea. Not a single locust was left in all the country of Egypt.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1798S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1798S\"></sup>hardened Pharaoh's heart, and he did not let the people of Israel go.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1799T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1799T\"></sup>“Stretch out your hand toward heaven, that there may be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1799U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1799U\"></sup>darkness over the land of Egypt, a darkness to be felt.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Moses stretched out his hand toward heaven, and there was pitch darkness in all the land of Egypt three days.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They did not see one another, nor did anyone rise from his place for three days, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1801V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1801V\"></sup>all the people of Israel had light where they lived.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Pharaoh called Moses and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1802W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1802W\"></sup>“Go, serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1802X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1802X\"></sup>your little ones also may go with you; only let your flocks and your herds remain behind.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Moses said, “You must also let us have sacrifices and burnt offerings, that we may sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Our livestock also must go with us; not a hoof shall be left behind, for we must take of them to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, and we do not know with what we must serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> until we arrive there.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1805Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1805Y\"></sup>hardened Pharaoh's heart, and he would not let them go.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to him, “Get away from me; take care never to see my face again, for on the day you see my face you shall die.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Moses said, “As you say! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1807Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1807Z\"></sup>I will not see your face again.”"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1808A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1808A\"></sup>one plague more I will bring upon Pharaoh and upon Egypt. Afterward he will let you go from here. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1808B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1808B\"></sup>When he lets you go, he will drive you away completely.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Speak now in the hearing of the people, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1809C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1809C\"></sup>they ask, every man of his neighbor and every woman of her neighbor, for silver and gold jewelry.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1810D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1810D\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians. Moreover, the man Moses was very great in the land of Egypt, in the sight of Pharaoh's servants and in the sight of the people.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Moses said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1811E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1811E\"></sup>‘About midnight I will go out in the midst of Egypt,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and every firstborn in the land of Egypt shall die, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sits on his throne, even to the firstborn of the slave girl who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1812F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1812F\"></sup>behind the handmill, and all the firstborn of the cattle.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1813G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1813G\"></sup>There shall be a great cry throughout all the land of Egypt, such as there has never been, nor ever will be again.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But not a dog shall growl <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1814H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1814H\"></sup>against any of the people of Israel, either man or beast, that you may know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1814I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1814I\"></sup>makes a distinction between Egypt and Israel.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1815J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1815J\"></sup>all these your servants shall come down to me and bow down to me, saying, ‘Get out, you and all the people who follow you.’ And after that I will go out.” And he went out from Pharaoh in hot anger.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1816K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1816K\"></sup>“Pharaoh will not listen to you, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1816L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1816L\"></sup>my wonders may be multiplied in the land of Egypt.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Moses and Aaron did all these wonders before Pharaoh, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1817M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1817M\"></sup>hardened Pharaoh's heart, and he did not let the people of Israel go out of his land."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1819A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1819A\"></sup>“This month shall be for you the beginning of months. It shall be the first month of the year for you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Tell all the congregation of Israel that on the tenth day of this month every man shall take a lamb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1820B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1820B\"></sup>according to their fathers' houses, a lamb for a household.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And if the household is too small for a lamb, then he and his nearest neighbor shall take according to the number of persons; according to what each can eat you shall make your count for the lamb.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your lamb shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1822C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1822C\"></sup>without blemish, a male a year old. You may take it from the sheep or from the goats,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and you shall keep it until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1823D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1823D\"></sup>fourteenth day of this month, when the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel shall kill their lambs at twilight.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Then they shall take some of the blood and put it on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1824E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1824E\"></sup>two doorposts and the lintel of the houses in which they eat it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They shall eat the flesh that night, roasted on the fire; with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1825F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1825F\"></sup>unleavened bread and bitter herbs they shall eat it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Do not eat any of it raw or boiled in water, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1826G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1826G\"></sup>roasted, its head with its legs and its inner parts.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1827H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1827H\"></sup>you shall let none of it remain until the morning; anything that remains until the morning you shall burn.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In this manner you shall eat it: with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1828I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1828I\"></sup>your belt fastened, your sandals on your feet, and your staff in your hand. And you shall eat it in haste. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1828J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1828J\"></sup>It is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s Passover.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1829K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1829K\"></sup>I will pass through the land of Egypt that night, and I will strike all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both man and beast; and on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1829L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1829L\"></sup>all the gods of Egypt I will execute judgments: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1829M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1829M\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1830N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1830N\"></sup>The blood shall be a sign for you, on the houses where you are. And when I see the blood, I will pass over you, and no plague will befall you to destroy you, when I strike the land of Egypt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“This day shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1831O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1831O\"></sup>for you a memorial day, and you shall keep it as a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; throughout your generations, as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1831P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1831P\"></sup>statute forever, you shall keep it as a feast.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1832Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1832Q\"></sup>Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread. On the first day you shall remove leaven out of your houses, for if anyone eats what is leavened, from the first day until the seventh day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1832R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1832R\"></sup>that person shall be cut off from Israel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>On the first day you shall hold a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1833S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1833S\"></sup>holy assembly, and on the seventh day a holy assembly. No work shall be done on those days. But what everyone needs to eat, that alone may be prepared by you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And you shall observe the Feast of Unleavened Bread, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1834T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1834T\"></sup>on this very day I brought your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1834U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1834U\"></sup>hosts out of the land of Egypt. Therefore you shall observe this day, throughout your generations, as a statute forever.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1835V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1835V\"></sup>In the first month, from the fourteenth day of the month at evening, you shall eat unleavened bread until the twenty-first day of the month at evening.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1836W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1836W\"></sup>For seven days no leaven is to be found in your houses. If anyone eats what is leavened, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1836X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1836X\"></sup>that person will be cut off from the congregation of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1836Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1836Y\"></sup>whether he is a sojourner or a native of the land.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You shall eat nothing leavened; in all your dwelling places you shall eat unleavened bread.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Moses called all the elders of Israel and said to them, “Go and select lambs for yourselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1838Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1838Z\"></sup>according to your clans, and kill the Passover lamb.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Take a bunch of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1839AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1839AA\"></sup>hyssop and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1839AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1839AB\"></sup>dip it in the blood that is in the basin, and touch <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1839AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1839AC\"></sup>the lintel and the two doorposts with the blood that is in the basin. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1839AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1839AD\"></sup>None of you shall go out of the door of his house until the morning.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1840AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1840AE\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will pass through to strike the Egyptians, and when he sees the blood on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1840AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1840AF\"></sup>the lintel and on the two doorposts, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will pass over the door and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1840AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1840AG\"></sup>will not allow the destroyer to enter your houses to strike you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall observe this rite as a statute for you and for your sons forever.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And when you come to the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1842AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1842AH\"></sup>as he has promised, you shall keep this service.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1843AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1843AI\"></sup>when your children say to you, ‘What do you mean by this service?’",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>you shall say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1844AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1844AJ\"></sup>‘It is the sacrifice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s Passover, for he passed over the houses of the people of Israel in Egypt, when he struck the Egyptians but spared our houses.’” And the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1844AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1844AK\"></sup>bowed their heads and worshiped.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the people of Israel went and did so; as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1846AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1846AL\"></sup>At midnight the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1846AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1846AM\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1846AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1846AN\"></sup>from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sat on his throne to the firstborn of the captive who was in the dungeon, and all the firstborn of the livestock.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Pharaoh rose up in the night, he and all his servants and all the Egyptians. And there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1847AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1847AO\"></sup>a great cry in Egypt, for there was not a house where someone was not dead.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he summoned Moses and Aaron by night and said, “Up, go out from among my people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1848AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1848AP\"></sup>both you and the people of Israel; and go, serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as you have said.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1849AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1849AQ\"></sup>Take your flocks and your herds, as you have said, and be gone, and bless me also!”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1850AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1850AR\"></sup>The Egyptians were urgent with the people to send them out of the land in haste. For they said, “We shall all be dead.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So the people took their dough before it was leavened, their kneading bowls being bound up in their cloaks on their shoulders.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The people of Israel had also done as Moses told them, for they had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1852AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1852AS\"></sup>asked the Egyptians for silver and gold jewelry and for clothing.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1853AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1853AT\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1853AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1853AU\"></sup>they let them have what they asked. Thus they plundered the Egyptians.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1854AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1854AV\"></sup>people of Israel journeyed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1854AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1854AW\"></sup>Rameses to Succoth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1854AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1854AX\"></sup>about six hundred thousand men on foot, besides women and children.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1855AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1855AY\"></sup>mixed multitude also went up with them, and very much livestock, both flocks and herds.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And they baked unleavened cakes of the dough that they had brought out of Egypt, for it was not leavened, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1856AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1856AZ\"></sup>they were thrust out of Egypt and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1856BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1856BA\"></sup>could not wait, nor had they prepared any provisions for themselves.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The time that the people of Israel lived in Egypt was 430 years.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>At the end of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1858BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1858BB\"></sup>430 years, on that very day, all the hosts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went out from the land of Egypt.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>It was a night of watching by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to bring them out of the land of Egypt; so this same night is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1859BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1859BC\"></sup>night of watching kept to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by all the people of Israel throughout their generations.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron, “This is the statute of the Passover: no foreigner shall eat of it,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>but every slave that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1861BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1861BD\"></sup>bought for money may eat of it after you have circumcised him.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1862BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1862BE\"></sup>No foreigner or hired worker may eat of it.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>It shall be eaten in one house; you shall not take any of the flesh outside the house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1863BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1863BF\"></sup>you shall not break any of its bones.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1864BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1864BG\"></sup>All the congregation of Israel shall keep it.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1865BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1865BH\"></sup>If a stranger shall sojourn with you and would keep the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, let all his males be circumcised. Then he may come near and keep it; he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1865BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1865BI\"></sup>shall be as a native of the land. But no uncircumcised person shall eat of it.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>There shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1866BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1866BJ\"></sup>one law for the native and for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1866BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1866BK\"></sup>stranger who sojourns among you.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>All the people of Israel did just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses and Aaron.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>And on that very day the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1868BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1868BL\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought the people of Israel out of the land of Egypt by their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1868BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1868BM\"></sup>hosts."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1870A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1870A\"></sup>“Consecrate to me all the firstborn. Whatever is the first to open the womb among the people of Israel, both of man and of beast, is mine.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Moses said to the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1871B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1871B\"></sup>“Remember this day in which you came out from Egypt, out of the house of slavery, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1871C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1871C\"></sup>for by a strong hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought you out from this place. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1871D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1871D\"></sup>No leavened bread shall be eaten.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Today, in the month of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1872E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1872E\"></sup>Abib, you are going out.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brings you into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1873F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1873F\"></sup>the land of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1873G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1873G\"></sup>he swore to your fathers to give you, a land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1873H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1873H\"></sup>flowing with milk and honey, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1873I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1873I\"></sup>you shall keep this service in this month.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1874J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1874J\"></sup>Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there shall be a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Unleavened bread shall be eaten for seven days; no leavened bread shall be seen with you, and no leaven shall be seen with you in all your territory.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1876K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1876K\"></sup>You shall tell your son on that day, ‘It is because of what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did for me when I came out of Egypt.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And it shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1877L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1877L\"></sup>be to you as a sign on your hand and as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1877M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1877M\"></sup>a memorial <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1877N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1877N\"></sup>between your eyes, that the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may be in your mouth. For with a strong hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought you out of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1878O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1878O\"></sup>You shall therefore keep this statute at its appointed time from year to year.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brings you into the land of the Canaanites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1879P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1879P\"></sup>as he swore to you and your fathers, and shall give it to you,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1880Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1880Q\"></sup>you shall set apart to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all that first opens the womb. All the firstborn of your animals that are males shall be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1881R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1881R\"></sup>Every firstborn of a donkey you shall redeem with a lamb, or if you will not redeem it you shall break its neck. Every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1881S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1881S\"></sup>firstborn of man among your sons you shall redeem.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1882T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1882T\"></sup>And when in time to come your son asks you, ‘What does this mean?’ you shall say to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1882U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1882U\"></sup>‘By a strong hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us out of Egypt, from the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1882V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1882V\"></sup>slavery.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For when Pharaoh stubbornly refused to let us go, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1883W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1883W\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> killed all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn of man and the firstborn of animals. Therefore I sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the males that first open the womb, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1883X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1883X\"></sup>all the firstborn of my sons I redeem.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1884Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1884Y\"></sup>It shall be as a mark on your hand or frontlets between your eyes, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1884Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1884Z\"></sup>by a strong hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us out of Egypt.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Pharaoh let the people go, God did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1885AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1885AA\"></sup>not lead them by way of the land of the Philistines, although that was near. For God said, “Lest the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1885AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1885AB\"></sup>change their minds when they see war and return to Egypt.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1886AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1886AC\"></sup>led the people around by the way of the wilderness toward the Red Sea. And the people of Israel went up out of the land of Egypt equipped for battle.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moses took the bones of Joseph with him, for Joseph had made the sons of Israel solemnly swear, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1887AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1887AD\"></sup>“God will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones with you from here.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1888AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1888AE\"></sup>they moved on from Succoth and encamped at Etham, on the edge of the wilderness.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1889AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1889AF\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went before them by day in a pillar of cloud to lead them along the way, and by night in a pillar of fire to give them light, that they might travel by day and by night.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The pillar of cloud by day and the pillar of fire by night did not depart from before the people."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Tell the people of Israel to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1892A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1892A\"></sup>turn back and encamp in front of Pi-hahiroth, between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1892B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1892B\"></sup>Migdol and the sea, in front of Baal-zephon; you shall encamp facing it, by the sea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For Pharaoh will say of the people of Israel, ‘They are wandering in the land; the wilderness has shut them in.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1894C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1894C\"></sup>I will harden Pharaoh's heart, and he will pursue them, and I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1894D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1894D\"></sup>get glory over Pharaoh and all his host, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1894E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1894E\"></sup>and the Egyptians shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And they did so.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the king of Egypt was told that the people had fled, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1895F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1895F\"></sup>mind of Pharaoh and his servants was changed toward the people, and they said, “What is this we have done, that we have let Israel go from serving us?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he made ready his chariot and took his army with him,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1897G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1897G\"></sup>six hundred chosen chariots and all the other chariots of Egypt with officers over all of them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1898H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1898H\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hardened the heart of Pharaoh king of Egypt, and he pursued the people of Israel while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1898I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1898I\"></sup>the people of Israel were going out defiantly.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1899J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1899J\"></sup>Egyptians pursued them, all Pharaoh's horses and chariots and his horsemen and his army, and overtook them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1899K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1899K\"></sup>encamped at the sea, by Pi-hahiroth, in front of Baal-zephon.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Pharaoh drew near, the people of Israel lifted up their eyes, and behold, the Egyptians were marching after them, and they feared greatly. And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1900L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1900L\"></sup>cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1901M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1901M\"></sup>said to Moses, “Is it because there are no graves in Egypt that you have taken us away to die in the wilderness? What have you done to us in bringing us out of Egypt?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Is not this what <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1902N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1902N\"></sup>we said to you in Egypt: ‘Leave us alone that we may serve the Egyptians’? For it would have been better for us to serve the Egyptians than to die in the wilderness.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Moses said to the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1903O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1903O\"></sup>“Fear not, stand firm, and see the salvation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he will work for you today. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1903P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1903P\"></sup>the Egyptians whom you see today, you shall never see again.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1904Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1904Q\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will fight for you, and you have only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1904R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1904R\"></sup>to be silent.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Why do you cry to me? Tell the people of Israel to go forward.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1906S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1906S\"></sup>Lift up your staff, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1906T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1906T\"></sup>stretch out your hand over the sea and divide it, that the people of Israel may go through the sea on dry ground.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1907U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1907U\"></sup>I will harden the hearts of the Egyptians so that they shall go in after them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1907V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1907V\"></sup>I will get glory over Pharaoh and all his host, his chariots, and his horsemen.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the Egyptians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1908W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1908W\"></sup>shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1908X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1908X\"></sup>when I have gotten glory over Pharaoh, his chariots, and his horsemen.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1909Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1909Y\"></sup>Then the angel of God who was going before the host of Israel moved and went behind them, and the pillar of cloud moved from before them and stood behind them,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>coming between the host of Egypt and the host of Israel. And there was the cloud and the darkness. And it lit up the night without one coming near the other all night.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1911Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1911Z\"></sup>stretched out his hand over the sea, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove the sea back by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1911AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1911AA\"></sup>a strong east wind all night and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1911AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1911AB\"></sup>made the sea dry land, and the waters were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1911AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1911AC\"></sup>divided.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1912AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1912AD\"></sup>the people of Israel went into the midst of the sea on dry ground, the waters being <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1912AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1912AE\"></sup>a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The Egyptians pursued and went in after them into the midst of the sea, all Pharaoh's horses, his chariots, and his horsemen.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And in the morning watch the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the pillar of fire and of cloud looked down on the Egyptian forces and threw the Egyptian forces into a panic,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>clogging their chariot wheels so that they drove heavily. And the Egyptians said, “Let us flee from before Israel, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1915AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1915AF\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fights for them against the Egyptians.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1916AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1916AG\"></sup>“Stretch out your hand over the sea, that the water may come back upon the Egyptians, upon their chariots, and upon their horsemen.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1917AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1917AH\"></sup>So Moses stretched out his hand over the sea, and the sea <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1917AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1917AI\"></sup>returned to its normal course when the morning appeared. And as the Egyptians fled into it, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1917AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1917AJ\"></sup>threw the Egyptians into the midst of the sea.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1918AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1918AK\"></sup>waters returned and covered the chariots and the horsemen; of all the host of Pharaoh that had followed them into the sea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1918AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1918AL\"></sup>not one of them remained.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1919AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1919AM\"></sup>people of Israel walked on dry ground through the sea, the waters being a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1920AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1920AN\"></sup>saved Israel that day from the hand of the Egyptians, and Israel saw the Egyptians dead on the seashore.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1921AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1921AO\"></sup>Israel saw the great power that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> used against the Egyptians, so the people feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1921AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1921AP\"></sup>believed in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in his servant Moses."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Then Moses and the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1922A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1922A\"></sup>sang this song to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1922B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1922B\"></sup>“I will sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he has triumphed gloriously;the horse and his rider he has thrown into the sea.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1923C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1923C\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my strength and my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1923D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1923D\"></sup>song,and he has become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1923E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1923E\"></sup>my salvation;this is my God, and I will praise him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1923F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1923F\"></sup>my father's God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1923G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1923G\"></sup>I will exalt him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1924H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1924H\"></sup>a man of war;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1924I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1924I\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is his name.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1925J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1925J\"></sup>“Pharaoh's chariots and his host he cast into the sea,and his chosen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1925K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1925K\"></sup>officers were sunk in the Red Sea.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1926L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1926L\"></sup>floods covered them;they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1926M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1926M\"></sup>went down into the depths like a stone.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1927N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1927N\"></sup>Your right hand, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, glorious in power,your right hand, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1927O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1927O\"></sup>shatters the enemy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1928P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1928P\"></sup>greatness of your majesty you overthrow your adversaries;you send out your fury; it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1928Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1928Q\"></sup>consumes them like stubble.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>At the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1929R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1929R\"></sup>blast of your nostrils the waters piled up;the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1929S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1929S\"></sup>floods stood up in a heap;the deeps congealed in the heart of the sea.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The enemy said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1930T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1930T\"></sup>‘I will pursue, I will overtake,I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1930U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1930U\"></sup>will divide the spoil, my desire shall have its fill of them.I will draw my sword; my hand shall destroy them.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1931V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1931V\"></sup>blew with your wind; the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1931W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1931W\"></sup>sea covered them;they sank like lead in the mighty waters.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1932X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1932X\"></sup>“Who is like you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, among the gods?Who is like you, majestic in holiness,awesome in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1932Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1932Y\"></sup>glorious deeds, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1932Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1932Z\"></sup>doing wonders?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You stretched out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1933AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1933AA\"></sup>your right hand;the earth swallowed them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“You have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1934AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1934AB\"></sup>led in your steadfast love the people whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1934AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1934AC\"></sup>you have redeemed;you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1934AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1934AD\"></sup>guided them by your strength to your holy abode.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1935AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1935AE\"></sup>The peoples have heard; they tremble;pangs have seized the inhabitants of Philistia.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now are the chiefs of Edom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1936AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1936AF\"></sup>dismayed;trembling seizes the leaders of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1936AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1936AG\"></sup>Moab;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1936AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1936AH\"></sup>all the inhabitants of Canaan have melted away.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Terror and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1937AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1937AI\"></sup>dread fall upon them;because of the greatness of your arm, they are still <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1937AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1937AJ\"></sup>as a stone,till your people, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, pass by,till the people pass by whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1937AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1937AK\"></sup>you have purchased.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You will bring them in and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1938AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1938AL\"></sup>plant them on your own mountain,the place, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which you have made for your abode,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1938AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1938AM\"></sup>the sanctuary, O Lord, which your hands have established.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1939AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1939AN\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will reign forever and ever.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1940AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1940AO\"></sup>the horses of Pharaoh with his chariots and his horsemen went into the sea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1940AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1940AP\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought back the waters of the sea upon them, but the people of Israel walked on dry ground in the midst of the sea.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1941AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1941AQ\"></sup>Miriam <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1941AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1941AR\"></sup>the prophetess, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1941AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1941AS\"></sup>sister of Aaron, took a tambourine in her hand, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1941AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1941AT\"></sup>all the women went out after her with tambourines and dancing.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Miriam sang to them:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1942AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1942AU\"></sup>“Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he has triumphed gloriously;the horse and his rider he has thrown into the sea.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Moses made Israel set out from the Red Sea, and they went into the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1943AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1943AV\"></sup>Shur. They went three days in the wilderness and found no water.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When they came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1944AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1944AW\"></sup>Marah, they could not drink the water of Marah because it was bitter; therefore it was named Marah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1945AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1945AX\"></sup>grumbled against Moses, saying, “What shall we drink?”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1946AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1946AY\"></sup>cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> showed him a log, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1946AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1946AZ\"></sup>threw it into the water, and the water became sweet.There the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made for them a statute and a rule, and there he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1946BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1946BA\"></sup>tested them,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1947BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1947BB\"></sup>“If you will diligently listen to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and do that which is right in his eyes, and give ear to his commandments and keep all his statutes, I will put none of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1947BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1947BC\"></sup>diseases on you that I put on the Egyptians, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1947BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1947BD\"></sup>your healer.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1948BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1948BE\"></sup>they came to Elim, where there were twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees, and they encamped there by the water."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1949A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1949A\"></sup>set out from Elim, and all the congregation of the people of Israel came to the wilderness of Sin, which is between Elim and Sinai, on the fifteenth day of the second month after they had departed from the land of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the whole congregation of the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1950B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1950B\"></sup>grumbled against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the people of Israel said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1951C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1951C\"></sup>“Would that we had died by the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the land of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1951D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1951D\"></sup>when we sat by the meat pots and ate bread to the full, for you have brought us out into this wilderness to kill this whole assembly with hunger.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Behold, I am about to rain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1952E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1952E\"></sup>bread from heaven for you, and the people shall go out and gather a day's portion every day, that I may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1952F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1952F\"></sup>test them, whether they will walk in my law or not.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>On the sixth day, when they prepare what they bring in, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1953G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1953G\"></sup>it will be twice as much as they gather daily.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Moses and Aaron said to all the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1954H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1954H\"></sup>“At evening <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1954I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1954I\"></sup>you shall know that it was the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who brought you out of the land of Egypt,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and in the morning you shall see the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1955J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1955J\"></sup>glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because he has heard your grumbling against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1955K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1955K\"></sup>what are we, that you grumble against us?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Moses said, “When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives you in the evening meat to eat and in the morning bread to the full, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has heard your grumbling that you grumble against him—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1956L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1956L\"></sup>what are we? Your grumbling is not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1956M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1956M\"></sup>against us but against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1957N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1957N\"></sup>said to Aaron, “Say to the whole congregation of the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1957O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1957O\"></sup>‘Come near before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he has heard your grumbling.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And as soon as Aaron spoke to the whole congregation of the people of Israel, they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1958P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1958P\"></sup>glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared in the cloud.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1960Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1960Q\"></sup>have heard the grumbling of the people of Israel. Say to them, ‘At <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1960R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1960R\"></sup>twilight you shall eat meat, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1960S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1960S\"></sup>in the morning you shall be filled with bread. Then you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>In the evening <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1961T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1961T\"></sup>quail came up and covered the camp, and in the morning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1961U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1961U\"></sup>dew lay around the camp.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And when the dew had gone up, there was on the face of the wilderness a fine, flake-like thing, fine as frost on the ground.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the people of Israel saw it, they said to one another, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1963V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1963V\"></sup>“What is it?” For they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1963W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1963W\"></sup>did not know what it was. And Moses said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1963X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1963X\"></sup>“It is the bread that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you to eat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded: ‘Gather of it, each one of you, as much as he can eat. You shall each take an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1964Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1964Y\"></sup>omer, according to the number of the persons that each of you has in his tent.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the people of Israel did so. They gathered, some more, some less.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But when they measured it with an omer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1966Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1966Z\"></sup>whoever gathered much had nothing left over, and whoever gathered little had no lack. Each of them gathered as much as he could eat.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Moses said to them, “Let no one leave any of it over till the morning.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But they did not listen to Moses. Some left part of it till the morning, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1968AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1968AA\"></sup>it bred worms and stank. And Moses was angry with them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Morning by morning they gathered it, each as much as he could eat; but when the sun grew hot, it melted.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>On <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1970AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1970AB\"></sup>the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread, two omers each. And when all the leaders of the congregation came and told Moses,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>he said to them, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded: ‘Tomorrow is a day of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1971AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1971AC\"></sup>solemn rest, a holy Sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; bake what you will bake and boil what you will boil, and all that is left over lay aside to be kept till the morning.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So they laid it aside till the morning, as Moses commanded them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1972AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1972AD\"></sup>it did not stink, and there were no worms in it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Moses said, “Eat it today, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1973AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1973AE\"></sup>today is a Sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; today you will not find it in the field.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Six days you shall gather it, but on the seventh day, which is a Sabbath, there will be none.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>On the seventh day some of the people went out to gather, but they found none.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1976AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1976AF\"></sup>“How long will you refuse to keep my commandments and my laws?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>See! The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you the Sabbath; therefore on the sixth day he gives you bread for two days. Remain each of you in his place; let no one go out of his place on the seventh day.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1978AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1978AG\"></sup>rested on the seventh day.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the house of Israel called its name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1979AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1979AH\"></sup>manna. It was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1979AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1979AI\"></sup>like coriander seed, white, and the taste of it was like wafers made with honey.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Moses said, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded: ‘Let an omer of it be kept throughout your generations, so that they may see the bread with which I fed you in the wilderness, when I brought you out of the land of Egypt.’”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And Moses said to Aaron, “Take a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1981AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1981AJ\"></sup>jar, and put an omer of manna in it, and place it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to be kept throughout your generations.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses, so Aaron placed it before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1982AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1982AK\"></sup>the testimony to be kept.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1983AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1983AL\"></sup>ate the manna forty years, till they came to a habitable land. They ate the manna till <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1983AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1983AM\"></sup>they came to the border of the land of Canaan.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>(An omer is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1984AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1984AN\"></sup>the tenth part of an ephah.)"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1985A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1985A\"></sup>All the congregation of the people of Israel moved on from the wilderness of Sin by stages, according to the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and camped at Rephidim, but there was no water for the people to drink.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1986B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1986B\"></sup>Therefore the people quarreled with Moses and said, “Give us water to drink.” And Moses said to them, “Why do you quarrel with me? Why do you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1986C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1986C\"></sup>test the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the people thirsted there for water, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1987D\"></sup>the people grumbled against Moses and said, “Why did you bring us up out of Egypt, to kill us and our children and our livestock with thirst?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Moses cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “What shall I do with this people? They are almost ready <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1988E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1988E\"></sup>to stone me.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Pass on before the people, taking with you some of the elders of Israel, and take in your hand the staff with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1989F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1989F\"></sup>which you struck the Nile, and go.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1990G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1990G\"></sup>Behold, I will stand before you there on the rock at Horeb, and you shall strike the rock, and water shall come out of it, and the people will drink.” And Moses did so, in the sight of the elders of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he called the name of the place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1991H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1991H\"></sup>Massah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1991I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1991I\"></sup>Meribah, because of the quarreling of the people of Israel, and because they tested the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by saying, “Is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> among us or not?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1992J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1992J\"></sup>Then Amalek came and fought with Israel at Rephidim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Moses said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1993K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1993K\"></sup>Joshua, “Choose for us men, and go out and fight with Amalek. Tomorrow I will stand on the top of the hill with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1993L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1993L\"></sup>the staff of God in my hand.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1994M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1994M\"></sup>Joshua did as Moses told him, and fought with Amalek, while Moses, Aaron, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1994N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1994N\"></sup>Hur went up to the top of the hill.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Whenever Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1995O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1995O\"></sup>held up his hand, Israel prevailed, and whenever he lowered his hand, Amalek prevailed.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Moses' hands grew weary, so they took a stone and put it under him, and he sat on it, while Aaron and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1996P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1996P\"></sup>Hur held up his hands, one on one side, and the other on the other side. So his hands were steady until the going down of the sun.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1997Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1997Q\"></sup>Joshua overwhelmed Amalek and his people with the sword.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Write this as a memorial in a book and recite it in the ears of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1998R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1998R\"></sup>Joshua, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1998S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1998S\"></sup>I will utterly blot out the memory of Amalek from under heaven.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1999T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1999T\"></sup>built an altar and called the name of it, The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Is My Banner,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>saying, “A hand upon the throne of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2000U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2000U\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will have war with Amalek from generation to generation.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2001A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2001A\"></sup>Jethro, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2001B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2001B\"></sup>the priest of Midian, Moses' father-in-law, heard of all that God had done for Moses and for Israel his people, how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had brought Israel out of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, had taken Zipporah, Moses' wife, after he had sent her home,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>along with her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2003C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2003C\"></sup>two sons. The name of the one was Gershom (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2003D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2003D\"></sup>for he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2003E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2003E\"></sup>“I have been a sojourner in a foreign land”),",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the name of the other, Eliezer (for he said, “The God of my father was my help, and delivered me from the sword of Pharaoh”).",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, came with his sons and his wife to Moses in the wilderness where he was encamped at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2005F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2005F\"></sup>mountain of God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And when he sent word to Moses, “I, your father-in-law Jethro, am coming to you with your wife and her two sons with her,”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2007G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2007G\"></sup>went out to meet his father-in-law and bowed down and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2007H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2007H\"></sup>kissed him. And they asked each other of their welfare and went into the tent.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Moses told his father-in-law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2008I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2008I\"></sup>all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done to Pharaoh and to the Egyptians for Israel's sake, all the hardship that had come upon them in the way, and how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had delivered them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jethro rejoiced for all the good that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done to Israel, in that he had delivered them out of the hand of the Egyptians.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jethro said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2010J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2010J\"></sup>“Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who has delivered you out of the hand of the Egyptians and out of the hand of Pharaoh and has delivered the people from under the hand of the Egyptians.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2011K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2011K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is greater than all gods, because in this affair they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2011L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2011L\"></sup>dealt arrogantly with the people.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Jethro, Moses' father-in-law, brought a burnt offering and sacrifices to God; and Aaron came with all the elders of Israel to eat bread with Moses' father-in-law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2012M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2012M\"></sup>before God.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The next day Moses sat to judge the people, and the people stood around Moses from morning till evening.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Moses' father-in-law saw all that he was doing for the people, he said, “What is this that you are doing for the people? Why do you sit alone, and all the people stand around you from morning till evening?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Moses said to his father-in-law, “Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2015N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2015N\"></sup>the people come to me to inquire of God;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2016O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2016O\"></sup>when they have a dispute, they come to me and I decide between one person and another, and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2016P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2016P\"></sup>make them know the statutes of God and his laws.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moses' father-in-law said to him, “What you are doing is not good.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You and the people with you will certainly wear yourselves out, for the thing is too heavy for you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2018Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2018Q\"></sup>You are not able to do it alone.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now obey my voice; I will give you advice, and God be with you! You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2019R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2019R\"></sup>represent the people before God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2019S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2019S\"></sup>bring their cases to God,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and you shall warn them about the statutes and the laws, and make them know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2020T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2020T\"></sup>the way in which they must walk and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2020U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2020U\"></sup>what they must do.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Moreover, look for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2021V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2021V\"></sup>able men from all the people, men who fear God, who are trustworthy and hate a bribe, and place such men over the people as chiefs of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties, and of tens.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2022W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2022W\"></sup>let them judge the people at all times. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2022X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2022X\"></sup>Every great matter they shall bring to you, but any small matter they shall decide themselves. So it will be easier for you, and they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2022Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2022Y\"></sup>bear the burden with you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>If you do this, God will direct you, you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2023Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2023Z\"></sup>able to endure, and all this people also will go to their place in peace.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Moses listened to the voice of his father-in-law and did all that he had said.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2025AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2025AA\"></sup>Moses chose able men out of all Israel and made them heads over the people, chiefs of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties, and of tens.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2026AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2026AB\"></sup>they judged the people at all times. Any hard case they brought to Moses, but any small matter they decided themselves.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then Moses let his father-in-law depart, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2027AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2027AC\"></sup>he went away to his own country."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>On the third new moon after the people of Israel had gone out of the land of Egypt, on that day they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2028A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2028A\"></sup>came into the wilderness of Sinai.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They set out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2029B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2029B\"></sup>Rephidim and came into the wilderness of Sinai, and they encamped in the wilderness. There Israel encamped before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2029C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2029C\"></sup>the mountain,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2030D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2030D\"></sup>Moses went up to God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2030E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2030E\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to him out of the mountain, saying, “Thus you shall say to the house of Jacob, and tell the people of Israel:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2031F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2031F\"></sup>‘You yourselves have seen what I did to the Egyptians, and how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2031G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2031G\"></sup>I bore you on eagles' wings and brought you to myself.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now therefore, if you will indeed obey my voice and keep my covenant, you shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2032H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2032H\"></sup>my treasured possession among all peoples, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2032I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2032I\"></sup>all the earth is mine;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and you shall be to me a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2033J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2033J\"></sup>kingdom of priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2033K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2033K\"></sup>a holy nation.’ These are the words that you shall speak to the people of Israel.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Moses came and called the elders of the people and set before them all these words that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2035L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2035L\"></sup>All the people answered together and said, “All that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken we will do.” And Moses reported the words of the people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Behold, I am coming to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2036M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2036M\"></sup>in a thick cloud, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2036N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2036N\"></sup>the people may hear when I speak with you, and may also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2036O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2036O\"></sup>believe you forever.”When Moses told the words of the people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go to the people and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2037P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2037P\"></sup>consecrate them today and tomorrow, and let them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2037Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2037Q\"></sup>wash their garments",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and be ready for the third day. For on the third day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2038R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2038R\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will come down on Mount Sinai in the sight of all the people.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And you shall set limits for the people all around, saying, ‘Take care not to go up into the mountain or touch the edge of it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2039S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2039S\"></sup>Whoever touches the mountain shall be put to death.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>No hand shall touch him, but he shall be stoned or shot; whether beast or man, he shall not live.’ When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2040T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2040T\"></sup>the trumpet sounds a long blast, they shall come up to the mountain.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2041U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2041U\"></sup>went down from the mountain to the people and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2041V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2041V\"></sup>consecrated the people; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2041W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2041W\"></sup>and they washed their garments.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he said to the people, “Be ready for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2042X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2042X\"></sup>third day; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2042Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2042Y\"></sup>do not go near a woman.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>On the morning of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2043Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2043Z\"></sup>third day there were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2043AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2043AA\"></sup>thunders and lightnings and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2043AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2043AB\"></sup>a thick cloud on the mountain and a very loud <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2043AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2043AC\"></sup>trumpet blast, so that all the people in the camp <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2043AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2043AD\"></sup>trembled.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2044AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2044AE\"></sup>Moses brought the people out of the camp to meet God, and they took their stand at the foot of the mountain.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2045AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2045AF\"></sup>Mount Sinai was wrapped in smoke because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had descended on it in fire. The smoke of it went up like the smoke of a kiln, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2045AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2045AG\"></sup>the whole mountain trembled greatly.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2046AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2046AH\"></sup>sound of the trumpet grew louder and louder, Moses spoke, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2046AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2046AI\"></sup>God answered him in thunder.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down on Mount Sinai, to the top of the mountain. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called Moses to the top of the mountain, and Moses went up.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go down and warn the people, lest they break through to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2048AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2048AJ\"></sup>to look and many of them perish.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Also let the priests who come near to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2049AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2049AK\"></sup>consecrate themselves, lest the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2049AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2049AL\"></sup>break out against them.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “The people cannot come up to Mount Sinai, for you yourself warned us, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2050AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2050AM\"></sup>‘Set limits around the mountain and consecrate it.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go down, and come up bringing Aaron with you. But do not let the priests and the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2051AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2051AN\"></sup>break through to come up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, lest he break out against them.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So Moses went down to the people and told them."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2053A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2053A\"></sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2053B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2053B\"></sup>God spoke all these words, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2054C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2054C\"></sup>“I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2055D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2055D\"></sup>“You shall have no other gods before me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2056E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2056E\"></sup>“You shall not make for yourself a carved image, or any likeness of anything that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth beneath, or that is in the water under the earth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2057F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2057F\"></sup>You shall not bow down to them or serve them, for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2057G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2057G\"></sup>a jealous God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2057H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2057H\"></sup>visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children to the third and the fourth generation of those who hate me,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but showing steadfast love to thousands of those who love me and keep my commandments.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2059I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2059I\"></sup>“You shall not take the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in vain, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not hold him guiltless who takes his name in vain.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2060J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2060J\"></sup>“Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2061K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2061K\"></sup>Six days you shall labor, and do all your work,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2062L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2062L\"></sup>seventh day is a Sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. On it you shall not do any work, you, or your son, or your daughter, your male servant, or your female servant, or your livestock, or the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2062M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2062M\"></sup>sojourner who is within your gates.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2063N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2063N\"></sup>in six days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made heaven and earth, the sea, and all that is in them, and rested on the seventh day. Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed the Sabbath day and made it holy.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2064O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2064O\"></sup>“Honor your father and your mother, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2064P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2064P\"></sup>that your days may be long in the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2065Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2065Q\"></sup>“You shall not murder.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2066R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2066R\"></sup>“You shall not commit adultery.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2067S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2067S\"></sup>“You shall not steal.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2068T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2068T\"></sup>“You shall not bear false witness against your neighbor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2069U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2069U\"></sup>“You shall not covet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2069V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2069V\"></sup>your neighbor's house; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2069W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2069W\"></sup>you shall not covet your neighbor's wife, or his male servant, or his female servant, or his ox, or his donkey, or anything that is your neighbor's.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now when all the people saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2070X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2070X\"></sup>the thunder and the flashes of lightning and the sound of the trumpet and the mountain smoking, the people were afraid and trembled, and they stood far off",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2071Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2071Y\"></sup>“You speak to us, and we will listen; but do not let God speak to us, lest we die.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2072Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2072Z\"></sup>Moses said to the people, “Do not fear, for God has come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2072AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2072AA\"></sup>test you, that the fear of him may be before you, that you may not sin.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The people stood far off, while Moses drew near to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2073AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2073AB\"></sup>thick darkness where God was.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Thus you shall say to the people of Israel: ‘You have seen for yourselves that I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2074AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2074AC\"></sup>talked with you from heaven.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2075AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2075AD\"></sup>You shall not make gods of silver to be with me, nor shall you make for yourselves gods of gold.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>An altar of earth you shall make for me and sacrifice on it your burnt offerings and your peace offerings, your sheep and your oxen. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2076AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2076AE\"></sup>In every place where I cause my name to be remembered I will come to you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2076AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2076AF\"></sup>bless you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2077AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2077AG\"></sup>If you make me an altar of stone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2077AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2077AH\"></sup>you shall not build it of hewn stones, for if you wield your tool on it you profane it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And you shall not go up by steps to my altar, that your nakedness be not exposed on it.’"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>“Now these are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2079A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2079A\"></sup>rules that you shall set before them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2080B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2080B\"></sup>When you buy a Hebrew slave, he shall serve six years, and in the seventh he shall go out free, for nothing.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If he comes in single, he shall go out single; if he comes in married, then his wife shall go out with him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If his master gives him a wife and she bears him sons or daughters, the wife and her children shall be her master's, and he shall go out alone.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2083C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2083C\"></sup>if the slave plainly says, ‘I love my master, my wife, and my children; I will not go out free,’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>then his master shall bring him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2084D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2084D\"></sup>God, and he shall bring him to the door or the doorpost. And his master shall bore his ear through with an awl, and he shall be his slave forever.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“When a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2085E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2085E\"></sup>sells his daughter as a slave, she shall not go out as the male slaves do.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If she does not please her master, who has designated her for himself, then he shall let her be redeemed. He shall have no right to sell her to a foreign people, since he has broken faith with her.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If he designates her for his son, he shall deal with her as with a daughter.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If he takes another wife to himself, he shall not diminish her food, her clothing, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2088F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2088F\"></sup>her marital rights.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And if he does not do these three things for her, she shall go out for nothing, without payment of money.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2090G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2090G\"></sup>“Whoever strikes a man so that he dies shall be put to death.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2091H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2091H\"></sup>But if he did not lie in wait for him, but God let him fall into his hand, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2091I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2091I\"></sup>I will appoint for you a place to which he may flee.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But if a man willfully attacks another to kill him by cunning, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2092J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2092J\"></sup>you shall take him from my altar, that he may die.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Whoever strikes his father or his mother shall be put to death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2094K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2094K\"></sup>“Whoever steals a man and sells him, and anyone found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2094L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2094L\"></sup>in possession of him, shall be put to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2095M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2095M\"></sup>“Whoever curses his father or his mother shall be put to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“When men quarrel and one strikes the other with a stone or with his fist and the man does not die but takes to his bed,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>then if the man rises again and walks outdoors with his staff, he who struck him shall be clear; only he shall pay for the loss of his time, and shall have him thoroughly healed.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“When a man strikes his slave, male or female, with a rod and the slave dies under his hand, he shall be avenged.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But if the slave survives a day or two, he is not to be avenged, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2099N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2099N\"></sup>slave is his money.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“When men strive together and hit a pregnant woman, so that her children come out, but there is no harm, the one who hit her shall surely be fined, as the woman's husband shall impose on him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2100O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2100O\"></sup>he shall pay as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2100P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2100P\"></sup>judges determine.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But if there is harm, then you shall pay <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2101Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2101Q\"></sup>life for life,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2102R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2102R\"></sup>eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>burn for burn, wound for wound, stripe for stripe.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“When a man strikes the eye of his slave, male or female, and destroys it, he shall let the slave go free because of his eye.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If he knocks out the tooth of his slave, male or female, he shall let the slave go free because of his tooth.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“When an ox gores a man or a woman to death, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2106S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2106S\"></sup>ox shall be stoned, and its flesh shall not be eaten, but the owner of the ox shall not be liable.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But if the ox has been accustomed to gore in the past, and its owner has been warned but has not kept it in, and it kills a man or a woman, the ox shall be stoned, and its owner also shall be put to death.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2108T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2108T\"></sup>a ransom is imposed on him, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2108U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2108U\"></sup>he shall give for the redemption of his life whatever is imposed on him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>If it gores a man's son or daughter, he shall be dealt with according to this same rule.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>If the ox gores a slave, male or female, the owner shall give to their master <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2110V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2110V\"></sup>thirty shekels of silver, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2110W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2110W\"></sup>the ox shall be stoned.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“When a man opens a pit, or when a man digs a pit and does not cover it, and an ox or a donkey falls into it,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the owner of the pit shall make restoration. He shall give money to its owner, and the dead beast shall be his.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“When one man's ox butts another's, so that it dies, then they shall sell the live ox and share its price, and the dead beast also they shall share.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Or if it is known that the ox has been accustomed to gore in the past, and its owner has not kept it in, he shall repay ox for ox, and the dead beast shall be his."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span> “If a man steals an ox or a sheep, and kills it or sells it, he shall repay five oxen for an ox, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2115A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2115A\"></sup>four sheep for a sheep.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup> If a thief is found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2116B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2116B\"></sup>breaking in and is struck so that he dies, there shall be no bloodguilt for him,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but if the sun has risen on him, there shall be bloodguilt for him. He shall surely pay. If he has nothing, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2117C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2117C\"></sup>he shall be sold for his theft.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If the stolen beast <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2118D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2118D\"></sup>is found alive in his possession, whether it is an ox or a donkey or a sheep, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2118E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2118E\"></sup>he shall pay double.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“If a man causes a field or vineyard to be grazed over, or lets his beast loose and it feeds in another man's field, he shall make restitution from the best in his own field and in his own vineyard.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“If fire breaks out and catches in thorns so that the stacked grain or the standing grain or the field is consumed, he who started the fire shall make full restitution.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“If a man gives to his neighbor money or goods to keep safe, and it is stolen from the man's house, then, if the thief is found, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2121F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2121F\"></sup>he shall pay double.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If the thief is not found, the owner of the house shall come near to God to show whether or not he has put his hand to his neighbor's property.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For every breach of trust, whether it is for an ox, for a donkey, for a sheep, for a cloak, or for any kind of lost thing, of which one says, ‘This is it,’ the case of both parties shall come before God. The one whom God condemns shall pay double to his neighbor.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“If a man gives to his neighbor a donkey or an ox or a sheep or any beast to keep safe, and it dies or is injured or is driven away, without anyone seeing it,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2125G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2125G\"></sup>an oath by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall be between them both to see whether or not he has put his hand to his neighbor's property. The owner shall accept the oath, and he shall not make restitution.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2126H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2126H\"></sup>it is stolen from him, he shall make restitution to its owner.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If it is torn by beasts, let him bring it as evidence. He shall not make restitution for what has been torn.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“If a man borrows anything of his neighbor, and it is injured or dies, the owner not being with it, he shall make full restitution.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>If the owner was with it, he shall not make restitution; if it was hired, it came for its hiring fee.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2130I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2130I\"></sup>“If a man seduces a virgin who is not betrothed and lies with her, he shall give the bride-price for her and make her his wife.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If her father utterly refuses to give her to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2131J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2131J\"></sup>he shall pay money equal to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2131K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2131K\"></sup>bride-price for virgins.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2132L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2132L\"></sup>“You shall not permit a sorceress to live.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2133M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2133M\"></sup>“Whoever lies with an animal shall be put to death.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2134N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2134N\"></sup>“Whoever sacrifices to any god, other than the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> alone, shall be devoted to destruction.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2135O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2135O\"></sup>“You shall not wrong a sojourner or oppress him, for you were sojourners in the land of Egypt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2136P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2136P\"></sup>You shall not mistreat any widow or fatherless child.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>If you do mistreat them, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2137Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2137Q\"></sup>cry out to me, I will surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2137R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2137R\"></sup>hear their cry,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and my wrath will burn, and I will kill you with the sword, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2138S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2138S\"></sup>your wives shall become widows and your children fatherless.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2139T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2139T\"></sup>“If you lend money to any of my people with you who is poor, you shall not be like a moneylender to him, and you shall not exact interest from him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2140U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2140U\"></sup>If ever you take your neighbor's cloak in pledge, you shall return it to him before the sun goes down,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>for that is his only covering, and it is his cloak for his body; in what else shall he sleep? And if he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2141V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2141V\"></sup>cries to me, I will hear, for I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2141W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2141W\"></sup>compassionate.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2142X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2142X\"></sup>“You shall not revile God, nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2142Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2142Y\"></sup>curse a ruler of your people.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“You shall not delay to offer from the fullness of your harvest and from the outflow of your presses. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2143Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2143Z\"></sup>The firstborn of your sons you shall give to me.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2144AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2144AA\"></sup>You shall do the same with your oxen and with your sheep: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2144AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2144AB\"></sup>seven days it shall be with its mother; on the eighth day you shall give it to me.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2145AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2145AC\"></sup>“You shall be consecrated to me. Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2145AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2145AD\"></sup>you shall not eat any flesh that is torn by beasts in the field; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2145AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2145AE\"></sup>you shall throw it to the dogs."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2146A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2146A\"></sup>“You shall not spread a false report. You shall not join hands with a wicked man to be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2146B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2146B\"></sup>malicious witness.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall not fall in with the many to do evil, nor shall you bear witness in a lawsuit, siding with the many, so as to pervert justice,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2148C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2148C\"></sup>nor shall you be partial to a poor man in his lawsuit.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2149D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2149D\"></sup>“If you meet your enemy's ox or his donkey going astray, you shall bring it back to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If you see the donkey of one who hates you lying down under its burden, you shall refrain from leaving him with it; you shall rescue it with him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2151E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2151E\"></sup>“You shall not pervert the justice due to your poor in his lawsuit.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2152F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2152F\"></sup>Keep far from a false charge, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2152G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2152G\"></sup>do not kill the innocent and righteous, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2152H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2152H\"></sup>I will not acquit the wicked.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2153I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2153I\"></sup>And you shall take no bribe, for a bribe blinds the clear-sighted and subverts the cause of those who are in the right.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2154J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2154J\"></sup>“You shall not oppress a sojourner. You know the heart of a sojourner, for you were sojourners in the land of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2155K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2155K\"></sup>“For six years you shall sow your land and gather in its yield,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>but the seventh year you shall let it rest and lie fallow, that the poor of your people may eat; and what they leave the beasts of the field may eat. You shall do likewise with your vineyard, and with your olive orchard.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2157L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2157L\"></sup>“Six days you shall do your work, but on the seventh day you shall rest; that your ox and your donkey may have rest, and the son of your servant woman, and the alien, may be refreshed.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2158M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2158M\"></sup>“Pay attention to all that I have said to you, and make no mention of the names of other gods, nor let it be heard on your lips.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2159N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2159N\"></sup>“Three times in the year you shall keep a feast to me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2160O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2160O\"></sup>You shall keep the Feast of Unleavened Bread. As I commanded you, you shall eat unleavened bread for seven days at the appointed time in the month of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2160P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2160P\"></sup>Abib, for in it you came out of Egypt. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2160Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2160Q\"></sup>None shall appear before me empty-handed.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall keep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2161R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2161R\"></sup>the Feast of Harvest, of the firstfruits of your labor, of what you sow in the field. You shall keep the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2161S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2161S\"></sup>Feast of Ingathering at the end of the year, when you gather in from the field the fruit of your labor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2162T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2162T\"></sup>Three times in the year shall all your males appear before the Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2163U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2163U\"></sup>“You shall not offer the blood of my sacrifice with anything leavened, or let the fat of my feast remain until the morning.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“The best of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2164V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2164V\"></sup>firstfruits of your ground you shall bring into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2164W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2164W\"></sup>“You shall not boil a young goat in its mother's milk.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2165X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2165X\"></sup>“Behold, I send an angel before you to guard you on the way and to bring you to the place that I have prepared.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Pay careful attention to him and obey his voice; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2166Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2166Y\"></sup>do not rebel against him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2166Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2166Z\"></sup>for he will not pardon your transgression, for my name is in him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“But if you carefully obey his voice and do all that I say, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2167AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2167AA\"></sup>I will be an enemy to your enemies and an adversary to your adversaries.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2168AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2168AB\"></sup>“When my angel goes before you and brings you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2168AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2168AC\"></sup>to the Amorites and the Hittites and the Perizzites and the Canaanites, the Hivites and the Jebusites, and I blot them out,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2169AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2169AD\"></sup>not bow down to their gods nor serve them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2169AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2169AE\"></sup>nor do as they do, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2169AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2169AF\"></sup>you shall utterly overthrow them and break their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2169AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2169AG\"></sup>pillars in pieces.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2170AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2170AH\"></sup>shall serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2170AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2170AI\"></sup>he will bless your bread and your water, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2170AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2170AJ\"></sup>I will take sickness away from among you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2171AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2171AK\"></sup>None shall miscarry or be barren in your land; I will fulfill the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2171AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2171AL\"></sup>number of your days.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2172AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2172AM\"></sup>my terror before you and will throw into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2172AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2172AN\"></sup>confusion all the people against whom you shall come, and I will make all your enemies turn their backs to you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2173AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2173AO\"></sup>I will send hornets before you, which shall drive out the Hivites, the Canaanites, and the Hittites from before you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2174AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2174AP\"></sup>I will not drive them out from before you in one year, lest the land become desolate and the wild beasts multiply against you.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Little by little I will drive them out from before you, until you have increased and possess the land.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2176AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2176AQ\"></sup>And I will set your border from the Red Sea to the Sea of the Philistines, and from the wilderness to the Euphrates, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2176AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2176AR\"></sup>I will give the inhabitants of the land into your hand, and you shall drive them out before you.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2177AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2177AS\"></sup>You shall make no covenant with them and their gods.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They shall not dwell in your land, lest they make you sin against me; for if you serve their gods, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2178AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2178AT\"></sup>it will surely be a snare to you.”"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Then he said to Moses, “Come up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you and Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2179A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2179A\"></sup>Nadab, and Abihu, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2179B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2179B\"></sup>seventy of the elders of Israel, and worship from afar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2180C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2180C\"></sup>alone shall come near to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but the others shall not come near, and the people shall not come up with him.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moses came and told the people all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2181D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2181D\"></sup>all the rules. And all the people answered with one voice and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2181E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2181E\"></sup>“All the words that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken we will do.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2182F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2182F\"></sup>Moses wrote down all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He rose early in the morning and built an altar at the foot of the mountain, and twelve <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2182G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2182G\"></sup>pillars, according to the twelve tribes of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he sent young men of the people of Israel, who offered burnt offerings and sacrificed peace offerings of oxen to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2184H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2184H\"></sup>Moses took half of the blood and put it in basins, and half of the blood he threw against the altar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he took the Book of the Covenant and read it in the hearing of the people. And they said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2185I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2185I\"></sup>“All that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken we will do, and we will be obedient.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2186J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2186J\"></sup>And Moses took the blood and threw it on the people and said, “Behold the blood of the covenant that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made with you in accordance with all these words.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses and Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2187K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2187K\"></sup>seventy of the elders of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2187L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2187L\"></sup>went up,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2188M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2188M\"></sup>saw the God of Israel. There was under his feet as it were a pavement of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2188N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2188N\"></sup>sapphire stone, like the very heaven for clearness.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he did not lay his hand on the chief men of the people of Israel; they beheld God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2189O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2189O\"></sup>ate and drank.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2190P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2190P\"></sup>“Come up to me on the mountain and wait there, that I may give you the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2190Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2190Q\"></sup>tablets of stone, with the law and the commandment, which I have written for their instruction.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Moses rose with his assistant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2191R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2191R\"></sup>Joshua, and Moses went up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2191S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2191S\"></sup>into the mountain of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he said to the elders, “Wait here for us until we return to you. And behold, Aaron and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2192T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2192T\"></sup>Hur are with you. Whoever has a dispute, let him go to them.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Moses went up on the mountain, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2193U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2193U\"></sup>the cloud covered the mountain.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2194V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2194V\"></sup>The glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dwelt on Mount Sinai, and the cloud covered it six days. And on the seventh day he called to Moses out of the midst of the cloud.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the appearance of the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was like a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2195W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2195W\"></sup>devouring fire on the top of the mountain in the sight of the people of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moses entered the cloud and went up on the mountain. And Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2196X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2196X\"></sup>was on the mountain forty days and forty nights."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2198A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2198A\"></sup>“Speak to the people of Israel, that they take for me a contribution. From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2198B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2198B\"></sup>every man whose heart moves him you shall receive the contribution for me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And this is the contribution that you shall receive from them: gold, silver, and bronze,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2200C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2200C\"></sup>blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen, goats' hair,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>tanned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2201D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2201D\"></sup>rams' skins, goatskins, acacia wood,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2202E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2202E\"></sup>oil for the lamps, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2202F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2202F\"></sup>spices for the anointing oil and for the fragrant incense,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>onyx stones, and stones for setting, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2203G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2203G\"></sup>ephod and for the breastpiece.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And let them make me a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2204H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2204H\"></sup>sanctuary, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2204I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2204I\"></sup>I may dwell in their midst.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2205J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2205J\"></sup>Exactly as I show you concerning the pattern of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2205K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2205K\"></sup>tabernacle, and of all its furniture, so you shall make it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2206L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2206L\"></sup>“They shall make an ark of acacia wood. Two cubits and a half shall be its length, a cubit and a half its breadth, and a cubit and a half its height.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall overlay it with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2207M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2207M\"></sup>pure gold, inside and outside shall you overlay it, and you shall make on it a molding of gold around it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You shall cast four rings of gold for it and put them on its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2208N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2208N\"></sup>four feet, two rings on the one side of it, and two rings on the other side of it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall make poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And you shall put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark to carry the ark by them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2211O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2211O\"></sup>poles shall remain in the rings of the ark; they shall not be taken from it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2212P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2212P\"></sup>And you shall put into the ark the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2212Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2212Q\"></sup>testimony that I shall give you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2213R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2213R\"></sup>“You shall make a mercy seat of pure gold. Two cubits and a half shall be its length, and a cubit and a half its breadth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And you shall make two cherubim of gold; of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2214S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2214S\"></sup>hammered work shall you make them, on the two ends of the mercy seat.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Make one cherub on the one end, and one cherub on the other end. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2215T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2215T\"></sup>Of one piece with the mercy seat shall you make the cherubim on its two ends.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2216U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2216U\"></sup>The cherubim shall spread out their wings above, overshadowing the mercy seat with their wings, their faces one to another; toward the mercy seat shall the faces of the cherubim be.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And you shall put the mercy seat on the top of the ark, and in the ark you shall put the testimony that I shall give you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2218V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2218V\"></sup>There I will meet with you, and from above the mercy seat, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2218W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2218W\"></sup>between the two cherubim that are on the ark of the testimony, I will speak with you about all that I will give you in commandment for the people of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2219X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2219X\"></sup>“You shall make a table of acacia wood. Two cubits shall be its length, a cubit its breadth, and a cubit and a half its height.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall overlay it with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2220Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2220Y\"></sup>pure gold and make a molding of gold around it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And you shall make a rim around it a handbreadth wide, and a molding of gold around the rim.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And you shall make for it four rings of gold, and fasten the rings to the four corners at its four legs.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Close to the frame the rings shall lie, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2223Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2223Z\"></sup>holders for the poles to carry the table.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You shall make the poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold, and the table shall be carried with these.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And you shall make its plates and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2225AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2225AA\"></sup>dishes for incense, and its flagons and bowls with which to pour drink offerings; you shall make them of pure gold.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And you shall set the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2226AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2226AB\"></sup>bread of the Presence on the table before me regularly.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2227AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2227AC\"></sup>“You shall make a lampstand of pure gold. The lampstand shall be made of hammered work: its base, its stem, its cups, its calyxes, and its flowers shall be of one piece with it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And there shall be six branches going out of its sides, three branches of the lampstand out of one side of it and three branches of the lampstand out of the other side of it;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>three cups made like almond blossoms, each with calyx and flower, on one branch, and three cups made like almond blossoms, each with calyx and flower, on the other branch—so for the six branches going out of the lampstand.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And on the lampstand itself there shall be four cups made like almond blossoms, with their calyxes and flowers,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and a calyx of one piece with it under each pair of the six branches going out from the lampstand.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Their calyxes and their branches shall be of one piece with it, the whole of it a single piece of hammered work of pure gold.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You shall make seven lamps for it. And the lamps <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2233AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2233AD\"></sup>shall be set up so as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2233AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2233AE\"></sup>to give light on the space in front of it.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Its tongs and their trays shall be of pure gold.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>It shall be made, with all these utensils, out of a talent of pure gold.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2236AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2236AF\"></sup>see that you make them after the pattern for them, which is being shown you on the mountain."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>“Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2237A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2237A\"></sup>you shall make the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2237B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2237B\"></sup>tabernacle with ten curtains of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2237C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2237C\"></sup>fine twined linen and blue and purple and scarlet yarns; you shall make them with cherubim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2237D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2237D\"></sup>skillfully worked into them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The length of each curtain shall be twenty-eight cubits, and the breadth of each curtain four cubits; all the curtains shall be the same size.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Five curtains shall be coupled to one another, and the other five curtains shall be coupled to one another.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And you shall make loops of blue on the edge of the outermost curtain in the first set. Likewise you shall make loops on the edge of the outermost curtain in the second set.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Fifty loops you shall make on the one curtain, and fifty loops you shall make on the edge of the curtain that is in the second set; the loops shall be opposite one another.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And you shall make fifty clasps of gold, and couple the curtains one to the other with the clasps, so that the tabernacle may be a single whole.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“You shall also make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2243E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2243E\"></sup>curtains of goats' hair for a tent over the tabernacle; eleven curtains shall you make.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The length of each curtain shall be thirty cubits, and the breadth of each curtain four cubits. The eleven curtains shall be the same size.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall couple five curtains by themselves, and six curtains by themselves, and the sixth curtain you shall double over at the front of the tent.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall make fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in one set, and fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in the second set.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“You shall make fifty clasps of bronze, and put the clasps into the loops, and couple the tent together that it may be a single whole.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the part that remains of the curtains of the tent, the half curtain that remains, shall hang over the back of the tabernacle.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the extra that remains in the length of the curtains, the cubit on the one side, and the cubit on the other side, shall hang over the sides of the tabernacle, on this side and that side, to cover it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2250F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2250F\"></sup>And you shall make for the tent a covering of tanned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2250G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2250G\"></sup>rams' skins and a covering of goatskins on top.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“You shall make upright frames for the tabernacle of acacia wood.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Ten cubits shall be the length of a frame, and a cubit and a half the breadth of each frame.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>There shall be two tenons in each frame, for fitting together. So shall you do for all the frames of the tabernacle.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall make the frames for the tabernacle: twenty frames for the south side;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and forty bases of silver you shall make under the twenty frames, two bases under one frame for its two tenons, and two bases under the next frame for its two tenons;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and for the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side twenty frames,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and their forty bases of silver, two bases under one frame, and two bases under the next frame.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And for the rear of the tabernacle westward you shall make six frames.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And you shall make two frames for corners of the tabernacle in the rear;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>they shall be separate beneath, but joined at the top, at the first ring. Thus shall it be with both of them; they shall form the two corners.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And there shall be eight frames, with their bases of silver, sixteen bases; two bases under one frame, and two bases under another frame.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“You shall make bars of acacia wood, five for the frames of the one side of the tabernacle,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and five bars for the frames of the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the frames of the side of the tabernacle at the rear westward.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The middle bar, halfway up the frames, shall run from end to end.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You shall overlay the frames with gold and shall make their rings of gold for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2265H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2265H\"></sup>holders for the bars, and you shall overlay the bars with gold.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then you shall erect the tabernacle <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2266I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2266I\"></sup>according to the plan for it that you were shown on the mountain.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2267J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2267J\"></sup>“And you shall make a veil of blue and purple and scarlet yarns and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2267K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2267K\"></sup>fine twined linen. It shall be made with cherubim <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2267L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2267L\"></sup>skillfully worked into it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And you shall hang it on four pillars of acacia overlaid with gold, with hooks of gold, on four bases of silver.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And you shall hang <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2269M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2269M\"></sup>the veil from the clasps, and bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2269N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2269N\"></sup>the ark of the testimony in there within the veil. And the veil shall separate for you the Holy Place from the Most Holy.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2270O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2270O\"></sup>You shall put the mercy seat on the ark of the testimony in the Most Holy Place.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2271P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2271P\"></sup>you shall set the table outside the veil, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2271Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2271Q\"></sup>lampstand on the south side of the tabernacle opposite the table, and you shall put the table on the north side.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“You shall make a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2272R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2272R\"></sup>screen for the entrance of the tent, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2272S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2272S\"></sup>blue and purple and scarlet yarns and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2272T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2272T\"></sup>fine twined linen, embroidered with needlework.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And you shall make for the screen five pillars of acacia, and overlay them with gold. Their hooks shall be of gold, and you shall cast five bases of bronze for them."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>“You shall make the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2274A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2274A\"></sup>altar of acacia wood, five cubits long and five cubits broad. The altar shall be square, and its height shall be three cubits.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2275B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2275B\"></sup>horns for it on its four corners; its horns shall be of one piece with it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2275C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2275C\"></sup>you shall overlay it with bronze.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall make pots for it to receive its ashes, and shovels and basins and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2276D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2276D\"></sup>forks and fire pans. You shall make all its utensils of bronze.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall also make for it a grating, a network of bronze, and on the net you shall make four bronze rings at its four corners.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And you shall set it under the ledge of the altar so that the net extends halfway down the altar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And you shall make poles for the altar, poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with bronze.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the poles shall be put through the rings, so that the poles are on the two sides of the altar when it is carried.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall make it hollow, with boards. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2281E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2281E\"></sup>As it has been shown you on the mountain, so shall it be made.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2282F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2282F\"></sup>“You shall make the court of the tabernacle. On the south side the court shall have hangings of fine twined linen a hundred cubits long for one side.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Its twenty pillars and their twenty bases shall be of bronze, but the hooks of the pillars and their fillets shall be of silver.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And likewise for its length on the north side there shall be hangings a hundred cubits long, its pillars twenty and their bases twenty, of bronze, but the hooks of the pillars and their fillets shall be of silver.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And for the breadth of the court on the west side there shall be hangings for fifty cubits, with ten pillars and ten bases.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The breadth of the court on the front to the east shall be fifty cubits.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The hangings for the one side of the gate shall be fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and three bases.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>On the other side the hangings shall be fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and three bases.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the gate of the court there shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2289G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2289G\"></sup>a screen twenty cubits long, of blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen, embroidered with needlework. It shall have four pillars and with them four bases.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All the pillars around the court shall be filleted with silver. Their hooks shall be of silver, and their bases of bronze.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The length of the court shall be a hundred cubits, the breadth fifty, and the height five cubits, with hangings of fine twined linen and bases of bronze.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>All the utensils of the tabernacle for every use, and all its pegs and all the pegs of the court, shall be of bronze.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2293H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2293H\"></sup>“You shall command the people of Israel that they bring to you pure beaten olive oil for the light, that a lamp may regularly be set up to burn.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2294I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2294I\"></sup>In the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2294J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2294J\"></sup>outside the veil that is before the testimony, Aaron and his sons shall tend it from evening to morning before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It shall be a statute forever to be observed throughout their generations by the people of Israel."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>“Then bring near to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2295A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2295A\"></sup>Aaron your brother, and his sons with him, from among the people of Israel, to serve me as priests—Aaron and Aaron's sons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2295B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2295B\"></sup>Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2296C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2296C\"></sup>And you shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother, for glory and for beauty.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall speak to all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2297D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2297D\"></sup>skillful, whom I have filled with a spirit of skill, that they make Aaron's garments to consecrate him for my priesthood.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>These are the garments that they shall make: a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2298E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2298E\"></sup>breastpiece, an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2298F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2298F\"></sup>ephod, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2298G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2298G\"></sup>a robe, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2298H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2298H\"></sup>a coat of checker work, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2298I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2298I\"></sup>a turban, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2298J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2298J\"></sup>a sash. They shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother and his sons to serve me as priests.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They shall receive <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2299K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2299K\"></sup>gold, blue and purple and scarlet yarns, and fine twined linen.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2300L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2300L\"></sup>“And they shall make the ephod of gold, of blue and purple and scarlet yarns, and of fine twined linen, skillfully worked.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It shall have two shoulder pieces attached to its two edges, so that it may be joined together.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2302M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2302M\"></sup>skillfully woven band on it shall be made like it and be of one piece with it, of gold, blue and purple and scarlet yarns, and fine twined linen.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall take two onyx stones, and engrave on them the names of the sons of Israel,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>six of their names on the one stone, and the names of the remaining six on the other stone, in the order of their birth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As a jeweler engraves signets, so shall you engrave the two stones with the names of the sons of Israel. You shall enclose them in settings of gold filigree.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And you shall set the two stones on the shoulder pieces of the ephod, as stones of remembrance for the sons of Israel. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2306N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2306N\"></sup>Aaron shall bear their names before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on his two shoulders <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2306O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2306O\"></sup>for remembrance.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall make settings of gold filigree,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and two chains of pure gold, twisted like cords; and you shall attach the corded chains to the settings.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2309P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2309P\"></sup>“You shall make a breastpiece of judgment, in skilled work. In the style of the ephod you shall make it—of gold, blue and purple and scarlet yarns, and fine twined linen shall you make it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>It shall be square and doubled, a span its length and a span its breadth.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2311Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2311Q\"></sup>You shall set in it four rows of stones. A row of sardius, topaz, and carbuncle shall be the first row;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and the second row an emerald, a sapphire, and a diamond;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and the third row a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and the fourth row a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They shall be set in gold filigree.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>There shall be twelve stones with their names according to the names of the sons of Israel. They shall be like signets, each engraved with its name, for the twelve tribes.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall make for the breastpiece twisted chains like cords, of pure gold.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And you shall make for the breastpiece two rings of gold, and put the two rings on the two edges of the breastpiece.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And you shall put the two cords of gold in the two rings at the edges of the breastpiece.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The two ends of the two cords you shall attach to the two settings of filigree, and so attach it in front to the shoulder pieces of the ephod.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>You shall make two rings of gold, and put them at the two ends of the breastpiece, on its inside edge next to the ephod.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And you shall make two rings of gold, and attach them in front to the lower part of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod, at its seam above the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2321R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2321R\"></sup>skillfully woven band of the ephod.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And they shall bind the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the ephod with a lace of blue, so that it may lie on the skillfully woven band of the ephod, so that the breastpiece shall not come loose from the ephod.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2323S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2323S\"></sup>So Aaron shall bear the names of the sons of Israel in the breastpiece of judgment on his heart, when he goes into the Holy Place, to bring them to regular <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2323T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2323T\"></sup>remembrance before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And in the breastpiece of judgment <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2324U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2324U\"></sup>you shall put the Urim and the Thummim, and they shall be on Aaron's heart, when he goes in before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Thus Aaron shall bear the judgment of the people of Israel on his heart before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regularly.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2325V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2325V\"></sup>“You shall make the robe of the ephod all of blue.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>It shall have an opening for the head in the middle of it, with a woven binding around the opening, like the opening in a garment, so that it may not tear.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>On its hem you shall make pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet yarns, around its hem, with bells of gold between them,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>a golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate, around the hem of the robe.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And it shall be on Aaron when he ministers, and its sound shall be heard when he goes into the Holy Place before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and when he comes out, so that he does not die.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“You shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2330W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2330W\"></sup>a plate of pure gold and engrave on it, like the engraving of a signet, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2330X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2330X\"></sup>‘Holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And you shall fasten it on the turban by a cord of blue. It shall be on the front of the turban.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>It shall be on Aaron's forehead, and Aaron shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2332Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2332Y\"></sup>bear any guilt from the holy things that the people of Israel consecrate as their holy gifts. It shall regularly be on his forehead, that they may be accepted before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“You shall weave the coat in checker work of fine linen, and you shall make a turban of fine linen, and you shall make a sash embroidered with needlework.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2334Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2334Z\"></sup>“For Aaron's sons you shall make coats and sashes and caps. You shall make them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2334AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2334AA\"></sup>for glory and beauty.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And you shall put them on Aaron your brother, and on his sons with him, and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2335AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2335AB\"></sup>anoint them and ordain them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2335AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2335AC\"></sup>consecrate them, that they may serve me as priests.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>You shall make for them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2336AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2336AD\"></sup>linen undergarments to cover their naked flesh. They shall reach from the hips to the thighs;",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and they shall be on Aaron and on his sons when they go into the tent of meeting or when they come near the altar to minister in the Holy Place, lest they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2337AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2337AE\"></sup>bear guilt and die. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2337AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2337AF\"></sup>This shall be a statute forever for him and for his offspring after him."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>“Now this is what you shall do to them to consecrate them, that they may serve me as priests. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2338A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2338A\"></sup>Take one bull of the herd and two rams without blemish,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2339B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2339B\"></sup>and unleavened bread, unleavened cakes mixed with oil, and unleavened wafers smeared with oil. You shall make them of fine wheat flour.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall put them in one basket and bring them in the basket, and bring the bull and the two rams.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall bring Aaron and his sons to the entrance of the tent of meeting and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2341C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2341C\"></sup>wash them with water.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2342D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2342D\"></sup>you shall take the garments, and put on Aaron the coat and the robe of the ephod, and the ephod, and the breastpiece, and gird him with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2342E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2342E\"></sup>skillfully woven band of the ephod.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2343F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2343F\"></sup>And you shall set the turban on his head and put the holy crown on the turban.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2344G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2344G\"></sup>the anointing oil and pour it on his head and anoint him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2345H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2345H\"></sup>shall bring his sons and put coats on them,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and you shall gird Aaron and his sons with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2346I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2346I\"></sup>sashes and bind caps on them. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2346J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2346J\"></sup>the priesthood shall be theirs by a statute forever. Thus you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2346K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2346K\"></sup>ordain Aaron and his sons.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Then you shall bring the bull before the tent of meeting. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2347L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2347L\"></sup>Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the bull.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then you shall kill the bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the entrance of the tent of meeting,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2349M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2349M\"></sup>shall take part of the blood of the bull and put it on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2349N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2349N\"></sup>horns of the altar with your finger, and the rest of the blood you shall pour out at the base of the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And you shall take all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2350O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2350O\"></sup>the fat that covers the entrails, and the long lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them, and burn them on the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But the flesh of the bull and its skin and its dung you shall burn with fire <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2351P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2351P\"></sup>outside the camp; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2351Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2351Q\"></sup>it is a sin offering.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2352R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2352R\"></sup>you shall take one of the rams, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2352S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2352S\"></sup>Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the ram,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and you shall kill the ram and shall take its blood and throw it against the sides of the altar.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2354T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2354T\"></sup>cut the ram into pieces, and wash its entrails and its legs, and put them with its pieces and its head,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and burn the whole ram on the altar. It is a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2355U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2355U\"></sup>pleasing aroma, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2356V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2356V\"></sup>“You shall take the other ram, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2356W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2356W\"></sup>and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the ram,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and you shall kill the ram and take part of its blood and put it on the tip of the right ear of Aaron and on the tips of the right ears of his sons, and on the thumbs of their right hands and on the great toes of their right feet, and throw the rest of the blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then you shall take part of the blood that is on the altar, and of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2358X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2358X\"></sup>anointing oil, and sprinkle it on Aaron and his garments, and on his sons and his sons' garments with him. He and his garments shall be holy, and his sons and his sons' garments with him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“You shall also take the fat from the ram and the fat tail and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2359Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2359Y\"></sup>fat that covers the entrails, and the long lobe of the liver and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them, and the right thigh (for it is a ram of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2359Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2359Z\"></sup>ordination),",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2360AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2360AA\"></sup>one loaf of bread and one cake of bread made with oil, and one wafer out of the basket of unleavened bread that is before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall put all these on the palms of Aaron and on the palms of his sons, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2361AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2361AB\"></sup>wave them for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2362AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2362AC\"></sup>you shall take them from their hands and burn them on the altar on top of the burnt offering, as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2362AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2362AD\"></sup>pleasing aroma before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It is a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“You shall take the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2363AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2363AE\"></sup>breast of the ram of Aaron's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2363AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2363AF\"></sup>ordination and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2363AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2363AG\"></sup>wave it for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and it shall be your portion.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And you shall consecrate the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2364AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2364AH\"></sup>breast of the wave offering that is waved and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2364AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2364AI\"></sup>thigh of the priests' portion that is contributed from the ram of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2364AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2364AJ\"></sup>ordination, from what was Aaron's and his sons'.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>It shall be for Aaron and his sons as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2365AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2365AK\"></sup>perpetual due from the people of Israel, for it is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2365AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2365AL\"></sup>contribution. It shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2365AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2365AM\"></sup>contribution from the people of Israel from their peace offerings, their contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“The holy garments of Aaron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2366AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2366AN\"></sup>shall be for his sons after him; they shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2366AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2366AO\"></sup>be anointed in them and ordained in them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The son who succeeds him as priest, who comes into the tent of meeting to minister in the Holy Place, shall wear them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2367AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2367AP\"></sup>seven days.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“You shall take the ram of ordination and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2368AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2368AQ\"></sup>boil its flesh in a holy place.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And Aaron and his sons shall eat the flesh of the ram and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2369AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2369AR\"></sup>bread that is in the basket in the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2370AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2370AS\"></sup>They shall eat those things with which atonement was made at their ordination and consecration, but an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2370AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2370AT\"></sup>outsider shall not eat of them, because they are holy.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And if any of the flesh for the ordination or of the bread remain until the morning, then you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2371AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2371AU\"></sup>burn the remainder with fire. It shall not be eaten, because it is holy.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“Thus you shall do to Aaron and to his sons, according to all that I have commanded you. Through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2372AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2372AV\"></sup>seven days shall you ordain them,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and every day you shall offer a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2373AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2373AW\"></sup>bull as a sin offering for atonement. Also you shall purify the altar, when you make atonement for it, and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2373AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2373AX\"></sup>anoint it to consecrate it.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Seven days you shall make atonement for the altar and consecrate it, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2374AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2374AY\"></sup>altar shall be most holy. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2374AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2374AZ\"></sup>Whatever touches the altar shall become holy.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“Now this is what you shall offer on the altar: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2375BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2375BA\"></sup>two lambs a year old <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2375BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2375BB\"></sup>day by day regularly.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>One lamb you shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2376BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2376BC\"></sup>in the morning, and the other lamb you shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2376BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2376BD\"></sup>at twilight.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And with the first lamb a tenth measure of fine flour mingled with a fourth of a hin of beaten oil, and a fourth of a hin of wine for a drink offering.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The other lamb you shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2378BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2378BE\"></sup>at twilight, and shall offer with it a grain offering and its drink offering, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2378BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2378BF\"></sup>in the morning, for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2378BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2378BG\"></sup>pleasing aroma, a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>It shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2379BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2379BH\"></sup>regular burnt offering throughout your generations at the entrance of the tent of meeting before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2379BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2379BI\"></sup>where I will meet with you, to speak to you there.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>There I will meet with the people of Israel, and it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2380BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2380BJ\"></sup>sanctified by my glory.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>I will consecrate the tent of meeting and the altar. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2381BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2381BK\"></sup>Aaron also and his sons I will consecrate to serve me as priests.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2382BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2382BL\"></sup>I will dwell among the people of Israel and will be their God.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And they shall know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2383BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2383BM\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, who brought them out of the land of Egypt that I might dwell among them. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2384A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2384A\"></sup>“You shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2384B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2384B\"></sup>an altar on which to burn incense; you shall make it of acacia wood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A cubit shall be its length, and a cubit its breadth. It shall be square, and two cubits shall be its height. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2385C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2385C\"></sup>Its horns shall be of one piece with it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2386D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2386D\"></sup>overlay it with pure gold, its top and around its sides and its horns. And you shall make a molding of gold around it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And you shall make two golden rings for it. Under its molding on two opposite sides of it you shall make them, and they shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2387E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2387E\"></sup>holders for poles with which to carry it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You shall make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And you shall put it in front of the veil that is above the ark of the testimony, in front of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2389F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2389F\"></sup>mercy seat that is above the testimony, where I will meet with you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Aaron shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2390G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2390G\"></sup>burn fragrant incense on it. Every morning when he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2390H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2390H\"></sup>dresses the lamps he shall burn it,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and when Aaron sets up the lamps at twilight, he shall burn it, a regular incense offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> throughout your generations.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall not offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2392I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2392I\"></sup>unauthorized incense on it, or a burnt offering, or a grain offering, and you shall not pour a drink offering on it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2393J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2393J\"></sup>Aaron shall make atonement on its horns once a year. With the blood of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2393K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2393K\"></sup>sin offering of atonement he shall make atonement for it once in the year throughout your generations. It is most holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2395L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2395L\"></sup>“When you take the census of the people of Israel, then each shall give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2395M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2395M\"></sup>a ransom for his life to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when you number them, that there be no plague among them when you number them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Each one who is numbered in the census shall give this: half a shekel according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2396N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2396N\"></sup>shekel of the sanctuary (the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2396O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2396O\"></sup>shekel is twenty gerahs), <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2396P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2396P\"></sup>half a shekel as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Everyone who is numbered in the census, from twenty years old and upward, shall give the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s offering.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The rich shall not give more, and the poor shall not give less, than <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2398Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2398Q\"></sup>the half shekel, when you give the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s offering to make atonement for your lives.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall take the atonement money from the people of Israel and shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2399R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2399R\"></sup>give it for the service of the tent of meeting, that it may bring the people of Israel to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2399S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2399S\"></sup>remembrance before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so as to make atonement for your lives.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“You shall also make a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2401T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2401T\"></sup>basin of bronze, with its stand of bronze, for washing. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2401U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2401U\"></sup>You shall put it between the tent of meeting and the altar, and you shall put water in it,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>with which Aaron and his sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2402V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2402V\"></sup>shall wash their hands and their feet.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When they go into the tent of meeting, or when they come near the altar to minister, to burn a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, they shall wash with water, so that they may not die.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They shall wash their hands and their feet, so that they may not die. It shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2404W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2404W\"></sup>be a statute forever to them, even to him and to his offspring throughout their generations.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Take the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2406X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2406X\"></sup>finest spices: of liquid myrrh 500 shekels, and of sweet-smelling cinnamon half as much, that is, 250, and 250 of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2406Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2406Y\"></sup>aromatic cane,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and 500 of cassia, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2407Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2407Z\"></sup>hin of olive oil.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And you shall make of these a sacred anointing oil blended as by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2408AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2408AA\"></sup>perfumer; it shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2408AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2408AB\"></sup>holy anointing oil.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2409AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2409AC\"></sup>With it you shall anoint the tent of meeting and the ark of the testimony,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and the table and all its utensils, and the lampstand and its utensils, and the altar of incense,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2411AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2411AD\"></sup>basin and its stand.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You shall consecrate them, that they may be most holy. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2412AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2412AE\"></sup>Whatever touches them will become holy.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2413AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2413AF\"></sup>You shall anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they may serve me as priests.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And you shall say to the people of Israel, ‘This shall be my holy anointing oil throughout your generations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>It shall not be poured on the body of an ordinary person, and you shall make no other like it in composition. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2415AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2415AG\"></sup>It is holy, and it shall be holy to you.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2416AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2416AH\"></sup>Whoever compounds any like it or whoever puts any of it on an outsider shall be cut off from his people.’”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2417AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2417AI\"></sup>“Take sweet spices, stacte, and onycha, and galbanum, sweet spices with pure frankincense (of each shall there be an equal part),",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and make an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2418AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2418AJ\"></sup>incense blended as by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2418AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2418AK\"></sup>perfumer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2418AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2418AL\"></sup>seasoned with salt, pure and holy.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>You shall beat some of it very small, and put part of it before the testimony in the tent of meeting <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2419AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2419AM\"></sup>where I shall meet with you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2419AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2419AN\"></sup>It shall be most holy for you.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And the incense that you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2420AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2420AO\"></sup>according to its composition, you shall not make for yourselves. It shall be for you holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2421AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2421AP\"></sup>Whoever makes any like it to use as perfume shall be cut off from his people.”"
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“See, I have called by name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2423A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2423A\"></sup>Bezalel the son of Uri, son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2423B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2423B\"></sup>Hur, of the tribe of Judah,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2424C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2424C\"></sup>filled him with the Spirit of God, with ability and intelligence, with knowledge and all craftsmanship,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>to devise artistic designs, to work in gold, silver, and bronze,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>in cutting stones for setting, and in carving wood, to work in every craft.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And behold, I have appointed with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2427D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2427D\"></sup>Oholiab, the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan. And I have given to all able men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2427E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2427E\"></sup>ability, that they may make all that I have commanded you:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2428F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2428F\"></sup>the tent of meeting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2428G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2428G\"></sup>the ark of the testimony, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2428H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2428H\"></sup>the mercy seat that is on it, and all the furnishings of the tent,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2429I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2429I\"></sup>the table and its utensils, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2429J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2429J\"></sup>the pure lampstand with all its utensils, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2429K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2429K\"></sup>the altar of incense,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2430L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2430L\"></sup>the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2430M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2430M\"></sup>the basin and its stand,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2431N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2431N\"></sup>the finely worked garments, the holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons, for their service as priests,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2432O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2432O\"></sup>the anointing oil and the fragrant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2432P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2432P\"></sup>incense for the Holy Place. According to all that I have commanded you, they shall do.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“You are to speak to the people of Israel and say, ‘Above all you shall keep my Sabbaths, for this is a sign between me and you throughout your generations, that you may know that I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, sanctify you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall keep the Sabbath, because it is holy for you. Everyone who profanes it shall be put to death. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2435Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2435Q\"></sup>Whoever does any work on it, that soul shall be cut off from among his people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2436R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2436R\"></sup>Six days shall work be done, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2436S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2436S\"></sup>the seventh day is a Sabbath of solemn rest, holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2436T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2436T\"></sup>Whoever does any work on the Sabbath day shall be put to death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Therefore the people of Israel shall keep the Sabbath, observing the Sabbath throughout their generations, as a covenant forever.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2438U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2438U\"></sup>It is a sign forever between me and the people of Israel that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2438V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2438V\"></sup>in six days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made heaven and earth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2438W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2438W\"></sup>on the seventh day he rested and was refreshed.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he gave to Moses, when he had finished speaking with him on Mount Sinai, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2439X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2439X\"></sup>two tablets of the testimony, tablets of stone, written with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2439Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2439Y\"></sup>the finger of God."
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>When the people saw that Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2440A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2440A\"></sup>delayed to come down from the mountain, the people gathered themselves together to Aaron and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2440B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2440B\"></sup>“Up, make us gods who shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2440C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2440C\"></sup>go before us. As for this Moses, the man who brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Aaron said to them, “Take off the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2441D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2441D\"></sup>rings of gold that are in the ears of your wives, your sons, and your daughters, and bring them to me.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So all the people took off the rings of gold that were in their ears and brought them to Aaron.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2443E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2443E\"></sup>And he received the gold from their hand and fashioned it with a graving tool and made a golden calf. And they said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2443F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2443F\"></sup>“These are your gods, O Israel, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Aaron saw this, he built an altar before it. And Aaron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2444G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2444G\"></sup>made a proclamation and said, “Tomorrow shall be a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they rose up early the next day and offered burnt offerings and brought peace offerings. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2445H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2445H\"></sup>the people sat down to eat and drink and rose up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2445I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2445I\"></sup>to play.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2446J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2446J\"></sup>“Go down, for your people, whom you brought up out of the land of Egypt, have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2446K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2446K\"></sup>corrupted themselves.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They have turned aside quickly out of the way that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2447L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2447L\"></sup>I commanded them. They have made for themselves a golden calf and have worshiped it and sacrificed to it and said, ‘These are your gods, O Israel, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt!’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “I have seen this people, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2448M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2448M\"></sup>it is a stiff-necked people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2449N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2449N\"></sup>let me alone, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2449O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2449O\"></sup>my wrath may burn hot against them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2449P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2449P\"></sup>I may consume them, in order that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2449Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2449Q\"></sup>I may make a great nation of you.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2450R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2450R\"></sup>Moses implored the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, why does your wrath burn hot against your people, whom you have brought out of the land of Egypt with great power and with a mighty hand?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2451S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2451S\"></sup>Why should the Egyptians say, ‘With evil intent did he bring them out, to kill them in the mountains and to consume them from the face of the earth’? Turn from your burning anger and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2451T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2451T\"></sup>relent from this disaster against your people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, your servants, to whom you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2452U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2452U\"></sup>swore by your own self, and said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2452V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2452V\"></sup>‘I will multiply your offspring as the stars of heaven, and all this land that I have promised I will give to your offspring, and they shall inherit it forever.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2453W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2453W\"></sup>relented from the disaster that he had spoken of bringing on his people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2454X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2454X\"></sup>Moses turned and went down from the mountain with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2454Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2454Y\"></sup>two tablets of the testimony in his hand, tablets that were written on both sides; on the front and on the back they were written.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2455Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2455Z\"></sup>The tablets were the work of God, and the writing was the writing of God, engraved on the tablets.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2456AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2456AA\"></sup>Joshua heard the noise of the people as they shouted, he said to Moses, “There is a noise of war in the camp.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But he said, “It is not the sound of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2457AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2457AB\"></sup>shouting for victory, or the sound of the cry of defeat, but the sound of singing that I hear.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And as soon as he came near the camp and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2458AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2458AC\"></sup>saw the calf and the dancing, Moses' anger burned hot, and he threw the tablets out of his hands and broke them at the foot of the mountain.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He took the calf that they had made and burned it with fire and ground it to powder and scattered it on the water and made the people of Israel drink it.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Moses said to Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2460AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2460AD\"></sup>“What did this people do to you that you have brought such a great sin upon them?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Aaron said, “Let not the anger of my lord burn hot. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2461AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2461AE\"></sup>You know the people, that they are set on evil.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2462AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2462AF\"></sup>they said to me, ‘Make us gods who shall go before us. As for this Moses, the man who brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2463AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2463AG\"></sup>I said to them, ‘Let any who have gold take it off.’ So they gave it to me, and I threw it into the fire, and out came this calf.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And when Moses saw that the people had broken loose (for Aaron had let them break loose, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2464AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2464AH\"></sup>to the derision of their enemies),",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>then Moses stood in the gate of the camp and said, “Who is on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s side? Come to me.” And all the sons of Levi gathered around him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, ‘Put your sword on your side each of you, and go to and fro from gate to gate throughout the camp, and each of you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2466AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2466AI\"></sup>kill his brother and his companion and his neighbor.’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And the sons of Levi did according to the word of Moses. And that day about three thousand men of the people fell.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Moses said, “Today you have been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2468AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2468AJ\"></sup>ordained for the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, each one at the cost of his son and of his brother, so that he might bestow a blessing upon you this day.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The next day Moses said to the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2469AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2469AK\"></sup>“You have sinned a great sin. And now I will go up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2469AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2469AL\"></sup>perhaps I can make atonement for your sin.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So Moses returned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “Alas, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2470AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2470AM\"></sup>this people has sinned a great sin. They have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2470AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2470AN\"></sup>made for themselves gods of gold.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But now, if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2471AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2471AO\"></sup>you will forgive their sin—but if not, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2471AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2471AP\"></sup>blot me out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2471AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2471AQ\"></sup>your book that you have written.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2472AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2472AR\"></sup>“Whoever has sinned against me, I will blot out of my book.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2473AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2473AS\"></sup>But now go, lead the people to the place about which I have spoken to you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2473AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2473AT\"></sup>behold, my angel shall go before you. Nevertheless, in the day when I visit, I will visit their sin upon them.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a plague on the people, because they made the calf, the one that Aaron made."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Depart; go up from here, you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2475A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2475A\"></sup>and the people whom you have brought up out of the land of Egypt, to the land of which I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, saying, ‘To <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2475B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2475B\"></sup>your offspring I will give it.’",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I will send an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2476C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2476C\"></sup>angel before you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2476D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2476D\"></sup>and I will drive out the Canaanites, the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2477E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2477E\"></sup>Go up to a land flowing with milk and honey; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2477F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2477F\"></sup>but I will not go up among you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2477G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2477G\"></sup>lest I consume you on the way, for you are a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2477H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2477H\"></sup>stiff-necked people.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the people heard this disastrous word, they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2478I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2478I\"></sup>mourned, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2478J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2478J\"></sup>no one put on his ornaments.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to Moses, “Say to the people of Israel, ‘You are a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2479K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2479K\"></sup>stiff-necked people; if for a single moment I should go up among you, I would <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2479L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2479L\"></sup>consume you. So now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2479M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2479M\"></sup>take off your ornaments, that I may know what to do with you.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Therefore the people of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments, from Mount Horeb onward.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Moses used to take the tent and pitch it outside the camp, far off from the camp, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2481N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2481N\"></sup>he called it the tent of meeting. And everyone who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2481O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2481O\"></sup>sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would go out to the tent of meeting, which was outside the camp.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Whenever Moses went out to the tent, all the people would rise up, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2482P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2482P\"></sup>each would stand at his tent door, and watch Moses until he had gone into the tent.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Moses entered the tent, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2483Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2483Q\"></sup>pillar of cloud would descend and stand at the entrance of the tent, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would speak with Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And when all the people saw the pillar of cloud standing at the entrance of the tent, all the people would rise up and worship, each at his tent door.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2485R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2485R\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> used to speak to Moses face to face, as a man speaks to his friend. When Moses turned again into the camp, his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2485S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2485S\"></sup>assistant Joshua the son of Nun, a young man, would not depart from the tent.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2486T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2486T\"></sup>you say to me, ‘Bring up this people,’ but you have not let me know whom you will send with me. Yet you have said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2486U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2486U\"></sup>‘I know you by name, and you have also found favor in my sight.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now therefore, if I have found favor in your sight, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2487V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2487V\"></sup>show me now your ways, that I may know you in order to find favor in your sight. Consider too that this nation is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2487W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2487W\"></sup>your people.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2488X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2488X\"></sup>“My presence will go with you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2488Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2488Y\"></sup>I will give you rest.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2489Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2489Z\"></sup>“If your presence will not go with me, do not bring us up from here.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For how shall it be known that I have found favor in your sight, I and your people? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2490AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2490AA\"></sup>Is it not in your going with us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2490AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2490AB\"></sup>so that we are distinct, I and your people, from every other people on the face of the earth?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “This very thing that you have spoken I will do, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2491AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2491AC\"></sup>for you have found favor in my sight, and I know you by name.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moses said, “Please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2492AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2492AD\"></sup>show me your glory.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2493AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2493AE\"></sup>“I will make all my goodness pass before you and will proclaim before you my name ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’ And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2493AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2493AF\"></sup>I will be gracious to whom I will be gracious, and will show mercy on whom I will show mercy.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But,” he said, “you cannot see my face, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2494AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2494AG\"></sup>man shall not see me and live.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Behold, there is a place by me where you shall stand on the rock,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and while my glory passes by I will put you in a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2496AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2496AH\"></sup>cleft of the rock, and I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2496AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2496AI\"></sup>cover you with my hand until I have passed by.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then I will take away my hand, and you shall see my back, but my face shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2497AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2497AJ\"></sup>not be seen.”"
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2498A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2498A\"></sup>“Cut for yourself two tablets of stone like the first, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2498B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2498B\"></sup>and I will write on the tablets the words that were on the first tablets, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2498C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2498C\"></sup>which you broke.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Be ready by the morning, and come up in the morning to Mount Sinai, and present yourself there to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2499D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2499D\"></sup>on the top of the mountain.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>No <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2500E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2500E\"></sup>one shall come up with you, and let no one be seen throughout all the mountain. Let no flocks or herds graze opposite that mountain.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Moses cut two tablets of stone like the first. And he rose early in the morning and went up on Mount Sinai, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him, and took in his hand two tablets of stone.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2502F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2502F\"></sup>descended in the cloud and stood with him there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2502G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2502G\"></sup>proclaimed the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> passed before him and proclaimed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2503H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2503H\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, a God merciful and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2503I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2503I\"></sup>gracious, slow to anger, and abounding in steadfast <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2503J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2503J\"></sup>love and faithfulness,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2504K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2504K\"></sup>keeping steadfast love for thousands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2504L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2504L\"></sup>forgiving iniquity and transgression and sin, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2504M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2504M\"></sup>who will by no means clear the guilty, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2504N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2504N\"></sup>visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children and the children's children, to the third and the fourth generation.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Moses quickly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2505O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2505O\"></sup>bowed his head toward the earth and worshiped.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he said, “If now I have found favor in your sight, O Lord, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2506P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2506P\"></sup>let the Lord go in the midst of us, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2506Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2506Q\"></sup>it is a stiff-necked people, and pardon our iniquity and our sin, and take us for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2506R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2506R\"></sup>your inheritance.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2507S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2507S\"></sup>I am making a covenant. Before all your people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2507T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2507T\"></sup>I will do marvels, such as have not been created in all the earth or in any nation. And all the people among whom you are shall see the work of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for it is an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2507U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2507U\"></sup>awesome thing that I will do with you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Observe what I command you this day. Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2508V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2508V\"></sup>I will drive out before you the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2509W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2509W\"></sup>Take care, lest you make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land to which you go, lest it become a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2509X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2509X\"></sup>snare in your midst.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2510Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2510Y\"></sup>tear down their altars and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2510Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2510Z\"></sup>break their pillars and cut down their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2510AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2510AA\"></sup>Asherim",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>(for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2511AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2511AB\"></sup>you shall worship no other god, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, whose name is Jealous, is a jealous God),",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2512AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2512AC\"></sup>lest you make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land, and when they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2512AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2512AD\"></sup>whore after their gods and sacrifice to their gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2512AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2512AE\"></sup>you are invited, you eat of his sacrifice,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and you take of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2513AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2513AF\"></sup>their daughters for your sons, and their daughters <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2513AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2513AG\"></sup>whore after their gods and make your sons whore after their gods.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2514AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2514AH\"></sup>“You shall not make for yourself any gods of cast metal.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2515AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2515AI\"></sup>“You shall keep the Feast of Unleavened Bread. Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, at the time appointed in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2515AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2515AJ\"></sup>the month Abib, for in the month Abib you came out from Egypt.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2516AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2516AK\"></sup>All that open the womb are mine, all your male livestock, the firstborn of cow and sheep.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2517AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2517AL\"></sup>firstborn of a donkey you shall redeem with a lamb, or if you will not redeem it you shall break its neck. All the firstborn of your sons you shall redeem. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2517AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2517AM\"></sup>none shall appear before me empty-handed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2518AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2518AN\"></sup>“Six days you shall work, but on the seventh day you shall rest. In plowing time and in harvest you shall rest.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2519AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2519AO\"></sup>You shall observe the Feast of Weeks, the firstfruits of wheat harvest, and the Feast of Ingathering at the year's end.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2520AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2520AP\"></sup>Three times in the year shall all your males appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, the God of Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2521AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2521AQ\"></sup>cast out nations before you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2521AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2521AR\"></sup>enlarge your borders; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2521AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2521AS\"></sup>no one shall covet your land, when you go up to appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God three times in the year.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2522AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2522AT\"></sup>“You shall not offer the blood of my sacrifice with anything leavened, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2522AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2522AU\"></sup>or let the sacrifice of the Feast of the Passover remain until the morning.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2523AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2523AV\"></sup>The best of the firstfruits of your ground you shall bring to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2523AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2523AW\"></sup>You shall not boil a young goat in its mother's milk.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Write these words, for in accordance with these words <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2524AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2524AX\"></sup>I have made a covenant with you and with Israel.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2525AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2525AY\"></sup>So he was there with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forty days and forty nights. He neither ate bread nor drank water. And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2525AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2525AZ\"></sup>wrote on the tablets the words of the covenant, the Ten Commandments.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When Moses came down from Mount Sinai, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2526BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2526BA\"></sup>the two tablets of the testimony in his hand as he came down from the mountain, Moses did not know that the skin of his face <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2526BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2526BB\"></sup>shone because he had been talking with God.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Aaron and all the people of Israel saw Moses, and behold, the skin of his face <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2527BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2527BC\"></sup>shone, and they were afraid to come near him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But Moses called to them, and Aaron and all the leaders of the congregation returned to him, and Moses talked with them.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Afterward all the people of Israel came near, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2529BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2529BD\"></sup>commanded them all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken with him in Mount Sinai.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And when Moses had finished speaking with them, he put a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2530BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2530BE\"></sup>veil over his face.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Whenever Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2531BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2531BF\"></sup>went in before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to speak with him, he would remove the veil, until he came out. And when he came out and told the people of Israel what he was commanded,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the people of Israel would see the face of Moses, that the skin of Moses' face was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2532BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2532BG\"></sup>shining. And Moses would put the veil over his face again, until he went in to speak with him."
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>Moses assembled all the congregation of the people of Israel and said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2533A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2533A\"></sup>“These are the things that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded you to do.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2534B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2534B\"></sup>Six days work shall be done, but on the seventh day you shall have a Sabbath of solemn rest, holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Whoever does any work on it shall be put to death.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2535C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2535C\"></sup>You shall kindle no fire in all your dwelling places on the Sabbath day.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moses said to all the congregation of the people of Israel, “This is the thing that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2537D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2537D\"></sup>Take from among you a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2537E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2537E\"></sup>Whoever is of a generous heart, let him bring the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s contribution: gold, silver, and bronze;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen; goats' hair,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>tanned rams' skins, and goatskins; acacia wood,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>oil for the light, spices for the anointing oil and for the fragrant incense,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and onyx stones and stones for setting, for the ephod and for the breastpiece.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2542F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2542F\"></sup>every skillful craftsman among you come and make all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2543G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2543G\"></sup>the tabernacle, its tent and its covering, its hooks and its frames, its bars, its pillars, and its bases;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2544H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2544H\"></sup>the ark with its poles, the mercy seat, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2544I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2544I\"></sup>veil of the screen;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2545J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2545J\"></sup>the table with its poles and all its utensils, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2545K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2545K\"></sup>bread of the Presence;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2546L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2546L\"></sup>the lampstand also for the light, with its utensils and its lamps, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2546M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2546M\"></sup>oil for the light;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2547N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2547N\"></sup>and the altar of incense, with its poles, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2547O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2547O\"></sup>and the anointing oil and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2547P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2547P\"></sup>fragrant incense, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2547Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2547Q\"></sup>the screen for the door, at the door of the tabernacle;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2548R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2548R\"></sup>the altar of burnt offering, with its grating of bronze, its poles, and all its utensils, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2548S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2548S\"></sup>basin and its stand;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2549T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2549T\"></sup>the hangings of the court, its pillars and its bases, and the screen for the gate of the court;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2550U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2550U\"></sup>the pegs of the tabernacle and the pegs of the court, and their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2550V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2550V\"></sup>cords;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2551W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2551W\"></sup>finely worked garments for ministering in the Holy Place, the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of his sons, for their service as priests.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then all the congregation of the people of Israel departed from the presence of Moses.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And they came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2553X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2553X\"></sup>everyone whose heart stirred him, and everyone whose spirit moved him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2553Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2553Y\"></sup>and brought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s contribution to be used for the tent of meeting, and for all its service, and for the holy garments.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they came, both men and women. All who were of a willing heart brought brooches and earrings and signet rings and armlets, all sorts of gold objects, every man dedicating an offering of gold to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2555Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2555Z\"></sup>every one who possessed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2555AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2555AA\"></sup>blue or purple or scarlet yarns or fine linen or goats' hair or tanned rams' skins or goatskins brought them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2556AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2556AB\"></sup>Everyone who could make a contribution of silver or bronze brought it as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s contribution. And every one who possessed acacia wood of any use in the work brought it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2557AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2557AC\"></sup>skillful woman spun with her hands, and they all brought what they had spun in blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>All the women <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2558AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2558AD\"></sup>whose hearts stirred them to use their skill spun the goats' hair.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2559AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2559AE\"></sup>leaders brought onyx stones and stones to be set, for the ephod and for the breastpiece,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and spices and oil for the light, and for the anointing oil, and for the fragrant incense.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2561AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2561AF\"></sup>All the men and women, the people of Israel, whose heart moved them to bring anything for the work that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded by Moses to be done brought it as a freewill offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2562AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2562AG\"></sup>Then Moses said to the people of Israel, “See, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has called by name Bezalel the son of Uri, son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and he has filled him with the Spirit of God, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2563AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2563AH\"></sup>skill, with intelligence, with knowledge, and with all craftsmanship,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>to devise artistic designs, to work in gold and silver and bronze,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>in cutting stones for setting, and in carving wood, for work in every skilled craft.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And he has inspired him to teach, both him and Oholiab the son of Ahisamach of the tribe of Dan.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>He has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2567AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2567AI\"></sup>filled them with skill to do every sort of work done by an engraver or by a designer or by an embroiderer in blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen, or by a weaver—by any sort of workman or skilled designer."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span>“Bezalel and Oholiab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2568A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2568A\"></sup>every craftsman in whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put skill and intelligence to know how to do any work in the construction of the sanctuary shall work in accordance with all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Moses called Bezalel and Oholiab and every craftsman in whose mind the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had put skill, everyone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2569B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2569B\"></sup>whose heart stirred him up to come to do the work.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they received from Moses all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2570C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2570C\"></sup>contribution that the people of Israel had brought for doing the work on the sanctuary. They still kept bringing him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2570D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2570D\"></sup>freewill offerings every morning,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>so that all the craftsmen who were doing every sort of task on the sanctuary came, each from the task that he was doing,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and said to Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2572E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2572E\"></sup>“The people bring much more than enough for doing the work that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded us to do.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Moses gave command, and word was proclaimed throughout the camp, “Let no man or woman do anything more for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2573F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2573F\"></sup>contribution for the sanctuary.” So the people were restrained from bringing,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>for the material they had was sufficient to do all the work, and more.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2575G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2575G\"></sup>And all the craftsmen among the workmen made the tabernacle with ten curtains. They were made of fine twined linen and blue and purple and scarlet yarns, with cherubim skillfully worked.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The length of each curtain was twenty-eight cubits, and the breadth of each curtain four cubits. All the curtains were the same size.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He coupled five curtains to one another, and the other five curtains he coupled to one another.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He made loops of blue on the edge of the outermost curtain of the first set. Likewise he made them on the edge of the outermost curtain of the second set.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He made fifty loops on the one curtain, and he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that was in the second set. The loops were opposite one another.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he made fifty clasps of gold, and coupled the curtains one to the other with clasps. So the tabernacle was a single whole.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He also made curtains of goats' hair for a tent over the tabernacle. He made eleven curtains.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The length of each curtain was thirty cubits, and the breadth of each curtain four cubits. The eleven curtains were the same size.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He coupled five curtains by themselves, and six curtains by themselves.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he made fifty loops on the edge of the outermost curtain of the one set, and fifty loops on the edge of the other connecting curtain.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he made fifty clasps of bronze to couple the tent together that it might be a single whole.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he made for the tent a covering of tanned rams' skins and goatskins.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2587H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2587H\"></sup>Then he made the upright frames for the tabernacle of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2587I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2587I\"></sup>acacia wood.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Ten cubits was the length of a frame, and a cubit and a half the breadth of each frame.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Each frame had two tenons for fitting together. He did this for all the frames of the tabernacle.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The frames for the tabernacle he made thus: twenty frames for the south side.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he made forty bases of silver under the twenty frames, two bases under one frame for its two tenons, and two bases under the next frame for its two tenons.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side, he made twenty frames",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and their forty bases of silver, two bases under one frame and two bases under the next frame.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For the rear of the tabernacle westward he made six frames.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He made two frames for corners of the tabernacle in the rear.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And they were separate beneath but joined at the top, at the first ring. He made two of them this way for the two corners.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>There were eight frames with their bases of silver: sixteen bases, under every frame two bases.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He made bars of acacia wood, five for the frames of the one side of the tabernacle,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and five bars for the frames of the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the frames of the tabernacle at the rear westward.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And he made the middle bar to run from end to end halfway up the frames.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And he overlaid the frames with gold, and made their rings of gold for holders for the bars, and overlaid the bars with gold.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2602J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2602J\"></sup>He made the veil of blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen; with cherubim skillfully worked into it he made it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And for it he made four pillars of acacia and overlaid them with gold. Their hooks were of gold, and he cast for them four bases of silver.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>He also made a screen for the entrance of the tent, of blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen, embroidered with needlework,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and its five pillars with their hooks. He overlaid their capitals, and their fillets were of gold, but their five bases were of bronze."
		},
		"37": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">37 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2606A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2606A\"></sup>Bezalel made the ark of acacia wood. Two cubits and a half was its length, a cubit and a half its breadth, and a cubit and a half its height.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he overlaid it with pure gold inside and outside, and made a molding of gold around it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he cast for it four rings of gold for its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2608B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2608B\"></sup>four feet, two rings on its one side and two rings on its other side.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he made poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark to carry the ark.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he made a mercy seat of pure gold. Two cubits and a half was its length, and a cubit and a half its breadth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he made two cherubim of gold. He made them of hammered work on the two ends of the mercy seat,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>one cherub on the one end, and one cherub on the other end. Of one piece with the mercy seat he made the cherubim on its two ends.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The cherubim spread out their wings above, overshadowing the mercy seat with their wings, with their faces one to another; toward the mercy seat were the faces of the cherubim.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2615C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2615C\"></sup>He also made the table of acacia wood. Two cubits was its length, a cubit its breadth, and a cubit and a half its height.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he overlaid it with pure gold, and made a molding of gold around it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he made a rim around it a handbreadth wide, and made a molding of gold around the rim.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He cast for it four rings of gold and fastened the rings to the four corners at its four legs.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Close to the frame were the rings, as holders for the poles to carry the table.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He made the poles of acacia wood to carry the table, and overlaid them with gold.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he made the vessels of pure gold that were to be on the table, its plates and dishes for incense, and its bowls and flagons with which to pour drink offerings.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2622D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2622D\"></sup>He also made the lampstand of pure gold. He made the lampstand of hammered work. Its base, its stem, its cups, its calyxes, and its flowers were of one piece with it.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And there were six branches going out of its sides, three branches of the lampstand out of one side of it and three branches of the lampstand out of the other side of it;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>three cups made like almond blossoms, each with calyx and flower, on one branch, and three cups made like almond blossoms, each with calyx and flower, on the other branch—so for the six branches going out of the lampstand.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And on the lampstand itself were four cups made like almond blossoms, with their calyxes and flowers,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and a calyx of one piece with it under each pair of the six branches going out of it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Their calyxes and their branches were of one piece with it. The whole of it was a single piece of hammered work of pure gold.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he made its seven lamps and its tongs and its trays of pure gold.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He made it and all its utensils out of a talent of pure gold.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2630E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2630E\"></sup>He made the altar of incense of acacia wood. Its length was a cubit, and its breadth was a cubit. It was square, and two cubits was its height. Its horns were of one piece with it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He overlaid it with pure gold, its top and around its sides and its horns. And he made a molding of gold around it,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and made two rings of gold on it under its molding, on two opposite sides of it, as holders for the poles with which to carry it.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2634F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2634F\"></sup>He made the holy anointing oil also, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2634G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2634G\"></sup>pure fragrant incense, blended as by the perfumer."
		},
		"38": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">38 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2635A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2635A\"></sup>He made the altar of burnt offering of acacia wood. Five cubits was its length, and five cubits its breadth. It was square, and three cubits was its height.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He made horns for it on its four corners. Its horns were of one piece with it, and he overlaid it with bronze.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he made all the utensils of the altar, the pots, the shovels, the basins, the forks, and the fire pans. He made all its utensils of bronze.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he made for the altar a grating, a network of bronze, under its ledge, extending halfway down.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He cast four rings on the four corners of the bronze grating as holders for the poles.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with bronze.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he put the poles through the rings on the sides of the altar to carry it with them. He made it hollow, with boards.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2642B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2642B\"></sup>He made the basin of bronze and its stand of bronze, from the mirrors of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2642C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2642C\"></sup>ministering women who ministered in the entrance of the tent of meeting.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2643D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2643D\"></sup>And he made the court. For the south side the hangings of the court were of fine twined linen, a hundred cubits;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>their twenty pillars and their twenty bases were of bronze, but the hooks of the pillars and their fillets were of silver.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And for the north side there were hangings of a hundred cubits; their twenty pillars and their twenty bases were of bronze, but the hooks of the pillars and their fillets were of silver.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And for the west side were hangings of fifty cubits, their ten pillars, and their ten bases; the hooks of the pillars and their fillets were of silver.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And for the front to the east, fifty cubits.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The hangings for one side of the gate were fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and three bases.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And so for the other side. On both sides of the gate of the court were hangings of fifteen cubits, with their three pillars and their three bases.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All the hangings around the court were of fine twined linen.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the bases for the pillars were of bronze, but the hooks of the pillars and their fillets were of silver. The overlaying of their capitals was also of silver, and all the pillars of the court were filleted with silver.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the screen for the gate of the court was embroidered with needlework in blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen. It was twenty cubits long and five cubits high in its breadth, corresponding to the hangings of the court.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And their pillars were four in number. Their four bases were of bronze, their hooks of silver, and the overlaying of their capitals and their fillets of silver.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And all the pegs for the tabernacle and for the court all around were of bronze.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>These are the records of the tabernacle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2655E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2655E\"></sup>the tabernacle of the testimony, as they were recorded at the commandment of Moses, the responsibility of the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2655F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2655F\"></sup>under the direction of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2656G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2656G\"></sup>Bezalel the son of Uri, son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah, made all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and with him was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2657H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2657H\"></sup>Oholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan, an engraver and designer and embroiderer in blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the gold that was used for the work, in all the construction of the sanctuary, the gold from the offering, was twenty-nine talents and 730 shekels, by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2658I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2658I\"></sup>the shekel of the sanctuary.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The silver from those of the congregation who were recorded was a hundred talents and 1,775 shekels, by the shekel of the sanctuary:",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2660J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2660J\"></sup>beka a head (that is, half a shekel, by the shekel of the sanctuary), for everyone who was listed in the records, from twenty years old and upward, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2660K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2660K\"></sup>603,550 men.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The hundred talents of silver were for casting the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2661L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2661L\"></sup>bases of the sanctuary and the bases of the veil; a hundred bases for the hundred talents, a talent a base.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And of the 1,775 shekels he made hooks for the pillars and overlaid their capitals and made fillets for them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The bronze that was offered was seventy talents and 2,400 shekels;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>with it he made the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2664M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2664M\"></sup>bases for the entrance of the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2664N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2664N\"></sup>the bronze altar and the bronze grating for it and all the utensils of the altar,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2665O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2665O\"></sup>bases around the court, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2665P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2665P\"></sup>bases of the gate of the court, all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2665Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2665Q\"></sup>pegs of the tabernacle, and all the pegs around the court."
		},
		"39": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">39 </span>From the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2666A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2666A\"></sup>blue and purple and scarlet yarns they made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2666B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2666B\"></sup>finely woven garments, for ministering in the Holy Place. They made the holy garments for Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2666C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2666C\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2667D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2667D\"></sup>He made the ephod of gold, blue and purple and scarlet yarns, and fine twined linen.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they hammered out gold leaf, and he cut it into threads to work into the blue and purple and the scarlet yarns, and into the fine twined linen, in skilled design.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They made for the ephod attaching shoulder pieces, joined to it at its two edges.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the skillfully woven band on it was of one piece with it and made like it, of gold, blue and purple and scarlet yarns, and fine twined linen, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They made the onyx stones, enclosed in settings of gold filigree, and engraved like the engravings of a signet, according to the names of the sons of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he set them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod to be stones of remembrance for the sons of Israel, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2673E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2673E\"></sup>He made the breastpiece, in skilled work, in the style of the ephod, of gold, blue and purple and scarlet yarns, and fine twined linen.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It was square. They made the breastpiece doubled, a span its length and a span its breadth when doubled.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And they set in it four rows of stones. A row of sardius, topaz, and carbuncle was the first row;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and the second row, an emerald, a sapphire, and a diamond;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They were enclosed in settings of gold filigree.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There were twelve stones with their names according to the names of the sons of Israel. They were like signets, each engraved with its name, for the twelve tribes.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And they made on the breastpiece twisted chains like cords, of pure gold.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they made two settings of gold filigree and two gold rings, and put the two rings on the two edges of the breastpiece.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they put the two cords of gold in the two rings at the edges of the breastpiece.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They attached the two ends of the two cords to the two settings of filigree. Thus they attached it in front to the shoulder pieces of the ephod.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then they made two rings of gold, and put them at the two ends of the breastpiece, on its inside edge next to the ephod.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And they made two rings of gold, and attached them in front to the lower part of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod, at its seam above the skillfully woven band of the ephod.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And they bound the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the ephod with a lace of blue, so that it should lie on the skillfully woven band of the ephod, and that the breastpiece should not come loose from the ephod, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2687F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2687F\"></sup>He also made the robe of the ephod woven all of blue,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and the opening of the robe in it was like the opening in a garment, with a binding around the opening, so that it might not tear.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>On the hem of the robe they made pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet yarns and fine twined linen.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They also made bells of pure gold, and put the bells between the pomegranates all around the hem of the robe, between the pomegranates—",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>a bell and a pomegranate, a bell and a pomegranate around the hem of the robe for ministering, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2692G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2692G\"></sup>They also made the coats, woven of fine <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2692H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2692H\"></sup>linen, for Aaron and his sons,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2693I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2693I\"></sup>turban of fine linen, and the caps of fine linen, and the linen undergarments of fine twined linen,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and the sash of fine twined linen and of blue and purple and scarlet yarns, embroidered with needlework, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2695J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2695J\"></sup>They made the plate of the holy crown of pure gold, and wrote on it an inscription, like the engraving of a signet, “Holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And they tied to it a cord of blue to fasten it on the turban above, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Thus all the work of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting was finished, and the people of Israel did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2697K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2697K\"></sup>according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses; so they did.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then they brought the tabernacle to Moses, the tent and all its utensils, its hooks, its frames, its bars, its pillars, and its bases;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the covering of tanned rams' skins and goatskins, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2699L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2699L\"></sup>veil of the screen;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the ark of the testimony with its poles and the mercy seat;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the table with all its utensils, and the bread of the Presence;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2702M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2702M\"></sup>the lampstand of pure gold and its lamps with the lamps set and all its utensils, and the oil for the light;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2703N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2703N\"></sup>the golden altar, the anointing oil and the fragrant incense, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2703O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2703O\"></sup>the screen for the entrance of the tent;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>the bronze altar, and its grating of bronze, its poles, and all its utensils; the basin and its stand;",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2705P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2705P\"></sup>the hangings of the court, its pillars, and its bases, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2705Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2705Q\"></sup>screen for the gate of the court, its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2705R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2705R\"></sup>cords, and its pegs; and all the utensils for the service of the tabernacle, for the tent of meeting;",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the finely worked garments for ministering in the Holy Place, the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of his sons for their service as priests.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2707S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2707S\"></sup>According to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses, so the people of Israel had done all the work.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And Moses saw all the work, and behold, they had done it; as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded, so had they done it. Then Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2708T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2708T\"></sup>blessed them."
		},
		"40": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">40 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“On the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2710A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2710A\"></sup>first day of the first month you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2710B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2710B\"></sup>erect the tabernacle of the tent of meeting.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And you shall put in it the ark of the testimony, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2711C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2711C\"></sup>screen the ark with the veil.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2712D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2712D\"></sup>you shall bring in the table and arrange it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2712E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2712E\"></sup>you shall bring in the lampstand and set up its lamps.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2713F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2713F\"></sup>And you shall put the golden altar for incense before the ark of the testimony, and set up the screen for the door of the tabernacle.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2714G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2714G\"></sup>You shall set the altar of burnt offering before the door of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2715H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2715H\"></sup>and place the basin between the tent of meeting and the altar, and put water in it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And you shall set up the court all around, and hang up the screen for the gate of the court.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Then you shall take the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2717I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2717I\"></sup>anointing oil and anoint the tabernacle and all that is in it, and consecrate it and all its furniture, so that it may become holy.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall also anoint <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2718J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2718J\"></sup>the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils, and consecrate the altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2718K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2718K\"></sup>so that the altar may become most holy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall also anoint the basin and its stand, and consecrate it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2720L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2720L\"></sup>Then you shall bring Aaron and his sons to the entrance of the tent of meeting and shall wash them with water",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and put on Aaron the holy garments. And you shall anoint him and consecrate him, that he may serve me as priest.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall bring his sons also and put coats on them,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2723M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2723M\"></sup>and anoint them, as you anointed their father, that they may serve me as priests. And their anointing shall admit them to a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2723N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2723N\"></sup>perpetual priesthood throughout their generations.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This Moses did; according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him, so he did.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In the first month in the second year, on the first day of the month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2725O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2725O\"></sup>the tabernacle was erected.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moses erected the tabernacle. He laid its bases, and set up its frames, and put in its poles, and raised up its pillars.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he spread the tent over the tabernacle and put the covering of the tent over it, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2728P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2728P\"></sup>took the testimony and put it into the ark, and put the poles on the ark and set the mercy seat above on the ark.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he brought the ark into the tabernacle and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2729Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2729Q\"></sup>set up the veil of the screen, and screened <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2729R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2729R\"></sup>the ark of the testimony, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2730S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2730S\"></sup>He put the table in the tent of meeting, on the north side of the tabernacle, outside the veil,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and arranged the bread on it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2732T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2732T\"></sup>He put the lampstand in the tent of meeting, opposite the table on the south side of the tabernacle,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2733U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2733U\"></sup>and set up the lamps before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2734V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2734V\"></sup>He put the golden altar in the tent of meeting before the veil,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and burned fragrant incense on it, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2736W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2736W\"></sup>He put in place the screen for the door of the tabernacle.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2737X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2737X\"></sup>And he set the altar of burnt offering at the entrance of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting, and offered on it the burnt offering and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2737Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2737Y\"></sup>grain offering, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2738Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2738Z\"></sup>He set the basin between the tent of meeting and the altar, and put water in it for washing,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>with which Moses and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2739AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2739AA\"></sup>Aaron and his sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2739AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2739AB\"></sup>washed their hands and their feet.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When they went into the tent of meeting, and when they approached the altar, they washed, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2741AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2741AC\"></sup>And he erected the court around the tabernacle and the altar, and set up the screen of the gate of the court. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2741AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2741AD\"></sup>Moses finished the work.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2742AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2742AE\"></sup>the cloud covered the tent of meeting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2742AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2742AF\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the tabernacle.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And Moses was not able to enter the tent of meeting because the cloud settled on it, and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the tabernacle.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Throughout all their journeys, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2744AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2744AG\"></sup>whenever the cloud was taken up from over the tabernacle, the people of Israel would set out.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2745AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2745AH\"></sup>if the cloud was not taken up, then they did not set out till the day that it was taken up.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>For the cloud of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was on the tabernacle by day, and fire was in it by night, in the sight of all the house of Israel throughout all their journeys."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;